\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid11886869 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Could you give me your full name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You - my full name is Edwin Burden - Edwin. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 \{ILLEGIBLE\} Close - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Albion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, Chipping Norton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You're a widower?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Could you tell me the year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname date}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Year}{\xmlattrvalue 1920}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Day}
{\xmlattrvalue 20}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Month}{\xmlattrvalue 11}}}November the twentieth 1920{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And the year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname date}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Month}{\xmlattrvalue 2}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Day}
{\xmlattrvalue 21}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Year}{\xmlattrvalue 1890}}}February the twenty-first, 1890{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And your birthplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Chipping Norton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Can you tell me how many years you lived in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I shall have to think about that. About three years. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So you were about three years old when you moved from that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Where did you go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Went up to a place called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Chapelhouse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 . Stayed there for a number of years then came back to Chipping Norton. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was Chapel House not in Chipping Norton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 It's a small village just outside Chipping Norton. And - afterwards came back from there and - lived in a place up - what is called 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Rock Hill{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and lived there for a number of years until the 1914 war started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You were still living there when the War started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. And - then - I went to the war three days after the - war started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your family continue living in that house throughout the war years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 For a time and then they moved down to - Addlestone in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Surrey{\*\xmlclose}. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were they there 'til the ending of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Not altogether - they - my father stayed there but my mother came back and lived back in Chipping Norton for a while. Yes. And - before the war started I belonged to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
first St.{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} John's Ambulance Brigade that was formed in Chipping Norton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you lived in Chapel House - is it called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Chapelhouse. Is a - is a village - it's the - it's the name of a village, not one house, Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you know how long you were there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were you at school while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. Yes. I can't remember just how long we were there but - it may be interesting to know that this Chapel House was a place where the coaches used to come through and stop. The stagecoaches and Queen {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}Victoria{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} came and stayed there one time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 It was the house in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Rock Hill{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 that you came back to after the time in Chapelhouse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Just one sister. I should have had one sister but she died before I was born. That was another sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 And the one you had, was she younger than you or older?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Two years younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 She was the one you used to learn music with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Can you tell me when the family moved when you were three years old why did they move house - do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
They went to Chapelhouse because my mother's father and mother were in rather poor circumstances so my father - and mother decided the best plan would be to go and live up Chapelhouse so that my mother could see to her mother and father. And be clos
e to them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Why did you move back from Chapelhouse then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well it was - that was after - there was some little trouble with - the owner of the house where my father lived. My father had made the place look ever so nice, he'd decorated it o
ut and inside and made it look ever so much nicer than - houses that were close to and so the owner of the house when he came round to collect the rent, he said - well your house is ever so much better than the others, I shall have to charge more rent. Yo
u see? Any my father had done all this himself. So my father said, well if that's the case I - you know - move out. And he got another - went back to the - to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Rock Hill
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When he moved from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Rock Hill{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 to Addlestone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 That was during the war - while I was away in the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Why did he move to Addlestone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I think the reason was because he - from the standpoint of work. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 There was work there you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Work at Addelstone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And there wasn't in Chipping Norton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh ye
s, there was work in Chipping Norton but he wanted a change of work you see, he went there - because he wanted this change of work. And of course it was during the war time and -
