There were two rooms downstairs - and - there were - three bedrooms, small bedrooms, and - just a little bit of a - well I don't know what you'd call it a pantry rather than a scullery and that was what it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would you say that one of the rooms what would be called nowadays a reception room - a front room type of thing or parlour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well you couldn't exactly call it that in the true sense of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 term}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 - because the - there was a little lobby came from the front door. It was a lobby rather than a - a reception place and then you came straight from the lobby into the living room and there was - the sitting room at the back of that you see, then
 you had to go upstairs along a little passage to go upstairs to bed and there was one -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was the sitting room used every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. No - no the living - no, I'm sorry - the living room was used every day. The sitting room occasionally. And - we u
sed - I used to go in there - and my sister used to go in there and practice the piano you see. And there was an incident one time maybe interesting. I remember my mother and I were - I was only a boy at the time - my mother and I were sitting and having 
a midday meal and we heard ooh such a thumping noise and it was - up }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 above}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 the stairway and - I run up the stairs to see what had happened and there were two great big volumes, two volumes of books }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  tumbled down onto the stairs off a shelf that was just up above the head room. And the books had been laid flat and we never found out how those books came }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 
off}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  that shelf. It was a mystery. We never found out what was the cause because - I can never think how those books could - have fallen. Because they were 
laid flat on the shelf and big books too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And there was nobody up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Nobody upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did anyone besides your father and mother and your sister live in the house at Rockhill?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Just - a while after my - grandmother - my - they left
 my grandmother and grandfather and then they had the grandfather and grandmother to live with them and grandfather and grandmother both died in that place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 That was your mother's people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, come - I remember coming home from school - and I got to a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
certain place}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 - half way for between the school and the home - one dinner time and a voice as plain as ever it can be said to me, your grandmother's dead. Yes, a voice came to me as plain as ever it could be. And when I got home my grandmother was d
ead. That was remarkable wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Had she been ailing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you tell your mother about that voice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When I got home mother was in the neighbour's place - she was so upset. And I went up the stairs you see and - I found my grandmo
ther all laid out. And of course I'd been used to going along to the shop where my father worked and - he used to make coffee there. I was used to hearing about death and seeing coffins and all that sort of thing so although a boy I didn't get the shock t
hat some people would have. Although of course it was a - a bit of a shock to grandmother had gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you tell your mother about the voice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What did she say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I - I can't just remember her reaction because I - she was rather upset you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I - not very plainly. As far as I - now I think about it, as far as I can remember I don't think I went to the funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember if you had special clothes - a special suit of mourning clothes or anything of that type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well no - I was never badly dressed really because - you see the father - my father wasn't too badly paid according to the times. And - we just had a band - a black band put round the sleeve you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Your grandparents came to stay in the house - were there any lodgers or anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
We just had one friend came and stayed with us in that same house just for a short period. She was ill, I can't remember her name now it was - was a friend of my mother
's. She was ill and she stayed with us for some time and then she - went back to her own home. That's all I can remember staying there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your mother pay anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did she do the washing at home or was it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh, she used to do the washing at home. And her - most of her - domestic things she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Nobody came in at all to help her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your mother mend and make the family clothes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. She didn't make the clothes but she used to mend them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your father do any knitting or sewing - some men did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You mean working in a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did he do any work in the way of sewing or tailoring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well he - he didn't do a lot in the house itself, he used to do a lot on th
e garden. He was a very good gardener and used to - bring home some wonderful flowers, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 carnations}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 or - carnations of all types, those beautiful variegated ones, the different types of - variegated carnations. Chrysanthemums and - the vegetable garden he used to do exceptionally well. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you ever need to buy vegetables for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Hardly ever, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did he have any livestock like hens or pugs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 He used to keep some pigs sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did he sell them or did he have them for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What he used to do, he used to reckon to have two pigs and one being sold paid for the other to come in the house you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did he cure the pig himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes, I remember I used to hate going down some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 winter times}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  to the place where he used to - do the curing and I had to hold the light for him to - to do the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 skewering}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 . I used to veritably hate it, yes. It seemed such a dismal sort of job in this poor light you see, because it was - that was in the wintertime when he was doing i
t in the wintertime. And then - we - used to hang the flitches up in one part of the house up against the wall, you see, and some people, they used to have a rack. We didn't have a rack but they used to have a rack up on the ceiling put the bacon - put a 
whole flitch of bacon up on a rack you see and the hams and it used to dry up there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 This wall you had it on - was that in the pantry or the living room or where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No, it was in a part of the living room that was - wasn't exactly showing i
n the sense - the same sense. You know, it was a partly hidden, not altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You say your mother didn't make the clothes for the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 She might have made some small - clothes, when they were small but not - not later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did she buy new clothes or secondhand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh, new clothes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Your family was in that sort of position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Can you remember where she bought them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - some of her clothes she bought from the Co-ops. The Co-ops had started then 
you see, and well started, they'd been on for some time. And some she bought from Webbs. Webbs at - they've shut down just now - from this new street alteration and she used to buy some from there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did she buy them for a special occasion or just when you needed them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well mainly for when she needed 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 There weren't certain times of the year when you got new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, well of course if - if the clothes got a little bit shabby - she - go and get some more clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What about shoes - did she buy shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. Oh yes, they - as far as we were concerned - we didn't have any trouble about clothes, we - we didn't go ragged or anything like that. But - at that time very often you'd see some - children with their toes sti
cking out of their boots and their shoes and perhaps - rags - their clothes were ragged and dirty and - often -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you play with those children or were you apart from them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - not a lot but we used to play with some of them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were your parents particular about who you played with or did they let you play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 As long as the - we didn't get with - boys who }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 wore a lot or anything like that. They didn't - make too much bones about who we played with. But -
 because they reckoned to teach us what we ought to do in the house, you see, in home and what we ought to do and what we had not ought to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What was their attitude to swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Swearing and - they were very - my father was very dead nuts agai
nst smoking. I remember having a tanning for - because - I smoked with a cousin of mine. I had a tanning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How old were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I should think I was somewhere about - well, eight. Somewhere about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What did you smoke - cigarette?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 A kind of a cigarette.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you make it yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How did you make it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - I can't just remember at the moment - it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 was m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 ade }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 
with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  - with leaves and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So your father gave you a tanning for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. And - I remember - one time my - a cousin of mine wanted me to go out what he called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 niggering}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
. About Christmastime and - I went to my Auntie's house, see, where; my cousin lived and - we blacked our faces, we got some burnt cork and blacked our faces and - of course when I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 got back}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 home it was a job to get this cork black off. Ooh, it was a terrible job to get this off and - ooh my mother went on to me and I can remember I was crying, the tears running down over this - this black and - my mother lifted m
e up and showed me in the, looking glass, in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 mirror}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  - and - I remember that. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What did you do with this niggering - you got your faces black and then what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well you'd got to - well, just sing some - sing songs you see only you - went as a - and pretend that you'd got a banjo you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did people give you money?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - we didn't get very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When your shoes needed repairing did your father repair them or were they taken to a shoemakers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No, there was an old cobbler
 named Allyn and - he was a very good old cobbler and - I used to go down and get these shoes when they were finished. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
But very often he - he used to like to sit and talk for a little while he was repairing the shoes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And - the remarkable thing about it wa
s I thought it was a dirty habit really, he used to put his tacks in his mouth and - he'd get his hammer and he'd do it as quick as this - and put those tacks in the shoes you see, round. And I thought, oh I shouldn't like to put things in my }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 mouth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  like th
at because my mother was always on about - anything being dirty you know. But - that's what he used to do and I've often wondered since you know - what his tongue must have been like and all that sort of thing. And - he used to make some - used to make so
m
e boots for my father with elastic sides. Because my father used to go out to meetings and coming to work and get ready for the meetings he wanted to be quick. And - but he could make boots - and I remember - I also when I was a boy used to go - there use
d
 to be a - a temperance choir and of course my father was teetotaller and - he - didn't like to think anything about - anybody drinking or anything like that. Rather strict with regard to myself he was. And - this temperance choir was got up to - practice
 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 tunes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  that were being - going to be played - sung at the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Crystal{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Palace{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. There was a bit festival at the Crystal Palace - do you remember - it was burned down years ago - and there was a - a man named Jeffers who was a saddler was the conductor and I remember we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 practising}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 a piece and the conductor was beating away, ooh, hour or so - ever so fast with his stick and all at once it came out of his hand and it hit me on the head. I always remember that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You were watching then were you when it hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I was singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You were actually in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And your father was too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And I was singing contralto. A boy you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And your father was in the same choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. He used to sing bass. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 And - talking of s
inging when we got a little older in that same house, my sister very often say would - either my sister or myself would play the piano and perhaps father would sing bass, I'd sing tenor, sister contralto and my mother the soprano. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And some of the people who - used to go by they used to say how it nice it sounded. Because our - our voices }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 blended}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  fairly well you see and - I often think about that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You had a piano in your home too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. You see, my - my sister and I started to play the pian
o. I think I was about nine and my sister of course two years younger and when we first started - I seemed to be going on, oh, ever so much faster than my sister. But later on the teacher put a piece in front of my sister to play and she played it straigh
t
 away and I couldn't. And somehow or other after that my sister went ahead of me. Yes. What she'd been doing you see was to - get all the rudiments and eventually when she got it she went on. And sometimes we'd play duets with - we - played duets as some 
of the little concerts you see. And - but she always had the hardest piece because I - played the other part you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Can you tell me about these little concerts, where they were given and all that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well I'll tell you what - the finest concert - 
you wouldn't be able to go to some of this - I've got some photographs that I'd like to show you sometime and - I think it would - according your time now so shall we do that later. I've - I've got some photographs of one thing and another that went on li
ke that. I've got quite a number of - postcards on -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
You were telling me your father did quite a lot in the garden - did he do anything in the house in the way of cooking or cleaning, washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well he didn't do much of that. He used to - if t
here was any repairs in the actual house you see and he - what he a called a man's work then he'd do that. He didn't do housework. And - and one thing -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Well I - I always used to do my mother's errands and - I used to go - do most of th
e errands and - also, in those days you see instead of having these knives and forks like you have today you had to clean them. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
They were just a plain metal you see and that was my job - my job on Saturday mornings to clean the knives and forks and I alway
s cleaned my mother's shoes and my father's boots. My sister used to clean her own. But that was my job on Saturday, clean my father's boots and - mother's shoes and do the knives and forks, get the errands - well any time the errands. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 And in those days you see - people were very narrow minded from a religious standpoint, it was supposed to be an awful thing to saw a button on Sundays, or to clean the shoes or to do anything like that see. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So this was done on Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would your sister have any jobs she had to do on a Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well she - she'd do certain things - help perhaps round in the house a bit and - I don't know whether she - she did a bit towards the cooking and all that. But she actually was a dressmaker. She used to make her own dress
es when she got older you see. She was a dressmaker. My wife was a dressmaker and worked at the same place. In fact my wife was a head dressmaker at the Co-op before I married her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you were a small boy do you remember your father ever giving you 
a bath or dressing you or undressing you or any of that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - no, my mother used to do that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember him telling you stories or reading to you or anything of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 He'd sometimes tell us stories and - but 
- he used to be rather particular on what I read. He didn't like me to read what he called trash you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What sort of things did he like you to read then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well he like me to - he liked me to read a - a - a story, not these so called blood and t
hunder they used to issue out in those days. One day he saw me reading a - a magazine called True Blue. And he took it - it was called the True Blue and they were some these - oh - it'd got stories in where they were shooting and killing and all that sort
 of thing and - he didn't like me reading those things. He took it off me and he said, next time I see you reading that, he said, I'll - shall give you a good hiding, he said. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember him ever taking you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
I remember - we - at the time we lived at Chapelhouse - he used to take me perhaps for a walk and - he'd carry me on his shoulders - what they called the cock o'lantern type, you know, and - I remember going down an avenue one time and a blackbir
d singing in a tree and that stands out in my mind, this blackbird was singing away there on a branch of this tree as we were going under. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
And then - that stands out in my memory - I was on his shoulder caught hold of his coat you know and - that stands out in my memory quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember going out with him in Chipping Norton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Some - some occasions. I remember he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 took}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  me took Earls Court Exhibition one time. I remember going up on the big wheel. And seeing that panoramic view of London 
and I remember a thing that stood out in my memory there as a boy - seeing a train going along right in the distance going like along the lines as we were up on the top of this big wheel at Earls Court.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How did you get up there - by train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You - oh yes, train. Oh you didn't get no transport. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Just you and your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. Yes. And - I remember - talking about trains and that sort of thing - travel rather, I remember seeing the first motor car. I was a little boy about four then. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were you excited by that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Oh yes. Oh - all the people were - you see that - and - of course it was - well it was an old bone-shaker I expect to what you'd - what you would reckon today. But they thought ooh that was fast as it went by.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And horses used to be frightened of them didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you ever remember your mother going out and leaving your father looking after you and your sister when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh - yes, well - sometimes that used to happen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When she went out where would she be off to when she went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well she'd go to perhaps some of her friends or she might go to some meeting. And - of course we used to have plenty of meetings in those days you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What sort of meetings were those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well, there were - meetings - there was a meetings that my father used to go to, what we called the Mutual Improvement and - that - that was held at the Baptist Chapel. The idea was to - further your education 'cos education in those da
ys didn't go so far as it does these days. And my father, you see, when he went to school he had to pay for his books. And I've got one or two books of his somewhere about now - he had to buy you see. And - they weren't bad books either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How often would he go to this Mutual Improvement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Perhaps once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your mother go too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
No. No. But mother - she'd perhaps go out as I said to some friends. Then perhaps there'd be some meetings at the chapel or some other place you see. She'd go to some of those meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were the Mutual Improvement meetings just for men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh for any one - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you know what they did at the meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 At the Mutual Improvement? Well perhaps they'd have some subject and discussion you see and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you do any little jobs for your sister to help her or did she do anything for you when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - I don't know - I can't think of anything. We - we used to - well sometimes had our little quarrels like - you know, little 
quarrels like everybody else and - then of course we'd play with each other and - do all sorts of things like that. And my sister was always - trying to - play up jokes you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 She had a sense of fun did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes, she was always trying to play up jokes and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You mean she'd try and tease you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Oh yes. I - I've - was sitting reading - one evening I - I'd got a book reading quietly there and all at once I found something }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 wet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  come on top of my head. Cold water all running down - things like that she'd do you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What would it be - a wet cloth or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 A - yes, she'd a - it was a sponge or something she'd got. Things like that she'd do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - in the early days somewhere around about - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}
{\xmlattrvalue 19}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}seven o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. Somewhere round about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Up to what age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh - I can't quite remember - later on we went to bed a bit later of course but I can't remember the - the - as far as age is concerned.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What about when you were ten or eleven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh about - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 10}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 11}}}ten eleven{\*\xmlclose} then we were about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0
}}}nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose} you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And when you were about five or six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh well, we went to bed fairly early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 About {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}seven o'clock{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 It was somewhere about that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your mother put you to bed or anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Oh yes. Mother - mother put - yes. When I was little - after I got a little older I had to go myself you see and - well, they reckoned to teach you to be self-reliant you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you have a room to yourself or did you share the room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Had a room to myself yes.- of course in the - in the early days when I was very, very young my sister and I used to share the same room.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 That would be at Chapelhouse would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No, not at Chapelhouse, we had a separate room at Chapelhouse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 It would be when you were a very little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You had your own room when you were at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Rock Hill
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And your sister had her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And what about the rooms - were your parents in the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, they had the other room, - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 In those days not many houses had bathrooms did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No, there was no bathroom there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What room did you bath in then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well we had to - had the bath in the - well, the sitting room - the living room rather you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When was it that you would have your bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh - well when I was small I remember my mother used to bath me pretty often. And - then the - as you got older it was 
about once a week you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was it always a certain night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well, not necessarily, no. We had to have one of those portable baths you see and in the winter - by the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When did you have clean clothes to put on in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh - every week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was that on a certain day of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Towards the weekend you see for to have clean things for the Sunday you see. Well collars and things like that perhaps you'd have more you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you have your meals in the living room in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 In the living room, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you ever eat in the sitting room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Hardly ever. Unless - unless it was a - we'd got a - say at Christmastime or a - if you'd got a party on - a birthday party, or something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Where did your mother cook - was the cooker in the living room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 The cooking was done in the living room, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What sort of cooker did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well, you see they'd got the old fashioned grates in those days and there was the grate i
n the middle and then a fairly big oven on one side and as a rule there was a container that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 contained}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 water, you could get hot water on the other side. In some places they'd got two ovens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 She had the one with the water container?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes, and
 then you see they had what they called the hob. At the top of the oven and they could hot a lot of things up on that you see and on the other side too. Then the kettle you see - you didn't - didn't get the electric kettles in those days, we got the - som
e people had got a hook and a bar across so you hung this kettle on the hook over the fire you see. And very often the kettle was put down over the gird to boil - or a saucepan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - breakfast - my sister and I used to have breakfast somewhere about - perhaps it would be {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. Well - my - the workmen at that - in those days - as long ago as - used to go to work at 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
 in the morning see. And - when they were on what they called short time they went to work on seven - at seven in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So would your father take something with him for breakfast or did he come back for it
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. Oh for the - when he went at six he used - they used to come home at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose} for breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 He'd come home and join you for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well of course mother used to have her breakfast when we did. Well you see as a rule you all had a breakfast together because we'd got to get to school at nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What did you have for breakfast in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Oh - very often perhaps fried egg and bacon and - you see, in those days you could get - I've known it when you could get twenty - twenty-two eggs for a shilling, you see, then of course you've got to realize that the wages proportionally - yes, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you have anything to drink with your egg and bacon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well we generally had tea, you see, tea for breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When was the main meal of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well in - in the middle of the day as a rule
. Yes. And except - if father had to go out anywhere you see - it used to be saved for him and - and warmed up. We always had ours {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose}, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Can you remember the sort of things your mother used to cook during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes, we used to have
 - you see father was a gardener - so we had potatoes and various vegetable and - perhaps beef sometimes, sometimes mutton and - sometimes - pork and sometimes liver.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you have a pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Sometimes mother used to make a - what they calle
d the jam roly pudding and then there was the pudding on the similar principle with currants or - or raising in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Like a spotted dog?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes. And sometimes there was the - that boiled pudding, just a plain pudding. And - used to make tarts - an
d jam tarts and nice pastry. Oh, used to get plenty of that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did she make her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. She didn't make her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 own bread}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 We used to have some bread from the Co-op and there was a - a baker named Christmas and we used to call him Father Christmas and - he\rquote 
d got a beard too but he was a remarkable good nature and I used to - there was a loaf they called the Coburg loaf, and I - you know they - they come up in - four cones isn't there - don't they. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 There was four cones each side of 
this loaf coming up - come up to a point and I used to love one of those pulled off and any amount of butter put on. I used to love that when I was a boy because that crust instead of being like it is today in some of the loaves like leather, it was all t
hat you could chew it and it was lovely really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When would you eat that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - say at - whenever the loaf came - at any meal time - teatime perhaps you see. 'Course my mother didn't like doing that really very much because she liked to cut the slices you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Did you have anything different on Sundays for {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 
12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} dinner?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - not all that different. Depended you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Anything different for breakfast on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well it depended - you see. We used to - it was tinned sometime
s you - you sometimes had porridge. Porridge for breakfast and - say, well sometimes a banana and something like that to - bread and butter you see and - of course some people they - they didn't have things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You were better off than the average?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Your father was a craftsman wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 For tea you'd have bread and butter would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, and jam. Yes, and cake. My mother was - made some very nice cakes you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did she make jam too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Sometimes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember her bottling fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 She didn't bottle fruit much. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Perhaps beetroot and onions. You'd perhaps bet the pickled beetroot and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
pickled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  onions. I remember while I had a cat as a boy and that cat loved eating this beetroot. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
It would be beetroot like anything with the vinegar on you know.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did she ever make any wine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No, you see we all - we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 teetotaler}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 . And - but she used to make a - a herb drink - occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was that for medicinal }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 purposes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  or refreshment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 For - for refreshment, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not for medicine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh no, no, it was a - it was non-alcoholic - herb drink you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did she make any medicines or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 remedies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you ever remember her having any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You didn't very often get the tinned vegetables and things then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you ever remember her buying tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not very often. I remember - I remember my father - and got r
ather a big job over at Ditchley and I was boy and it was a big job it lasted for quite a time and he was working there during the time they were rounding up the deer and he used to bring home - very often bring home some pieces of - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 venison}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  you see. We used to have venison - venison pie and I used to be very fond of the rabbit. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Rabbit pie I loved and I didn't like hare.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your father get the rabbits from Ditchley too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh no, you could get rabbits very cheap. They - you could get them at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 poulterer's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  and - even grocers very often used to sell rabbits an poultry as well you see and - they were fairly cheap, rabbits because - most -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did anyone in your family go poaching at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No, not poaching, no. No. I used to keep tame rabbits when I was a boy and white mice and - I had some guinea pigs, yes, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you ever remember your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - there was hardly any need for that not to us but some people had to do that and 
some - some people you see, they were placed like this - now take masons for instance. When it was very bad }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 weather}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 they couldn't work - and they couldn't - they weren't paid. A mason - a - yes. Yes, they built - what they used to build with the stone and 
- yes, you see, and - very often they were out of work quite a lot in the winter. Well then you see in the summer they used to have to work overtime if they could and try and pay off their bills, you see. And - some of them were very poor sometimes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you ever remember your father having a bigger helping than the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
No, he was - he wasn't - he wasn't a man who'd - either drink too much or eat too much and - as a matter of fact if he was giving anything away he'd nearly always give the best away to somebody. Yes. He - he - he'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 ne'er}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 give anybody - away anything he thought wasn't nice you see. And I think that sometimes he'd give people vegetables and - if there was somebody a bit poor and they hadn't got much I remember he used to send 
me with some vegetables to - to a poor old couple and he'd never send anything that was - that he thought wasn't nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were you allowed to talk }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 during}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  meals when you were a small boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well we could talk but my father didn't like us - tittering a
nd - and misbehaving. We were supposed to behave at the table. He didn't mind us talking in the ordinary way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 If your mother cooked the food could you choose what you wanted or did you have to have everything she cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - she used to try to make you have - especially greens. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
Because she said that's good for you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But there was no real forcing. She - she tried to make you have a - oh she fed us well and she looked after us well like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 If she gave you some food and you didn't eat it what would happen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - of course some of it was wasted and if it was not too bad it was sent - be done up again in some other way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Off your plates you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, yes. If - if it was - if it wasn't messed about. Of course if it was messed about she'd throw it away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 If it wasn't messed about she would serve it up at another meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well if - if she could work it in - do something, you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would she make you eat it at another meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not like that you know. Oh no, no force - no - there was no force in that way. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 If there was something on the table that you wanted that was out of reach, say the salt, could you ask for it to be passed to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh - oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Could you ask for a second helping.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - you - sometimes I used to have a second helping but - mother used to say you - you mustn't eat too much like that you know - admonish you a little big but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 To sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Nothing about the sitting, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 They didn't mind if you had your elbows on the table and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh, oh yes, she didn't like to see that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No, you had to sit up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes - keep your elbows down. Keep your elbows down and - keep in a decent position like that, yes. Yes.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would you bring a toy or a book to the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No. There's only - there's one thing that they used to go on to me about quite a lot and I'd got
 a cat and that cat always used to - see I'd be sitting up at the table and of course I wasn't - quite so big as I am now and I'm not very big now but you see my knees were down from the edge of the table quite a bit and this cat always used to come and l
ay on my lap while I was having my meal. They used to - go on about it quite a bit. They didn't make me - put the cat off but mother reckoned it wasn't healthy for me to have this cat - while I was having my meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - was supposed to finish the meal and wait until they'd finished theirs you see and - if you wanted to get down you - from the the table well you asked and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 As a rule. As a rule. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
Depended if someone else came to dinner you see or - anything like that but as a rule you generally sat in the same place.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you quite often have people to dinner then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not a lot but we used to have some friends come in occasionally you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would that be to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Sometimes yes. Yes. And we used to have - relatives coming to tea very often. And sometimes supper - there was one relative, a cousin of my father's - who was very friendly with my mother and she used to come up
 most - Sunday nights for a long time used to come - until she was ill - used to come up most Sunday nights and have supper with us. And then she'd come in - we'd go in for the - like I told you, we'd have a sing, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 She sang too did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When she came she'd have supper would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes, she'd have supper. Well we used to have supper then, well I shouldn't want to eat it now like we used to then, you'd have meat and - and perhaps some tart, pastry and go to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 bed on}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What sort of time would that be that you'd have supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh somewhere about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose} or - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}
nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose} at night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So you had breakfast, dinner - tea and supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 All through the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - you didn't alwa
ys have a supper like that - like I was saying - didn't always have a supper like that but sometimes you'd have - I'll tell you what my mother would sometimes get, she was very fond of sprats. We'd perhaps have some sprats for supper, well I didn't dream 
of having that for my supper now you see. Or - or any - think like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But it was usually something in the way of meat or fish was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 cheese}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  and sometimes pickles you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Anything to drink with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Very often cocoa. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Nearly always had cocoa.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When she served up the meal did she always serve you in the same order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well not necessarily, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Your father wasn't served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not necessarily.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was she the sort of person who showed affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes, yes. Oh - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 If you were worried about things could you tell her about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. And - there's another thing really when I got older. When I was out in the war, it
 was rather remarkable - I could always tell when she was worried. Kind of a telepathy really - always tell when she was worried.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you write to her then frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh I used to write pretty often yes, yes. But - but I didn't always get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
letters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  back because - sometimes the letters would go astray you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was your father an easy person to talk to or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not quite so easy as mother. No. But - but he - well he'd - he'd talk to you if he wanted to talk to you but - sometimes if you as
ked him questions he was busy - he didn't want to talk you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would you say you were closer to your mother or closer to him or was it the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well I don't know which I was - I daresay we did - if there was a toss up I expect my mother would be a little bit closer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But you got on well with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was he the sort of person who showed affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 More or less but not over }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 fussed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  - not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 over fussed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 , no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Could you tell him your worries if you were worried about things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh - yes, yes. Either of them you see. Either - either mother or father yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well they expect - expected to - well, you'd to be decent and - well live a decent li
fe then generally. That's what they expected of you. They expected you to be a good citizen and by being a good citizen see well you'd give them - proper behaviour as well wouldn't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did they bring you up to behave towards your sister in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Oh yes. I - I remember one time I was - rather - I'm rather ashamed of it - my sister and I had a little bit of a bother and I smacked her. And my father came and smacked me and told me not to do that again, not to hit a woman - not to hit a gir
l you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Suppose another child hit you and you told your parents, what would they say to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Now I'll tell you about an incident like that happened. What would I be - somewhere about twelve perhaps. And I'd got a cousin who was a little older than me and he was - I was - well, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
never liked}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 fighting and he was always - pushing me about. And one day he - knocked me about and I went in crying in home and my father was in there and wanted to know what was the matter and I told him. He said, 
well look, he said, my boy - the next time he does that you give him a good hiding or else I'll give you one. You see. And the next time he did it I did do that. See well I - I didn't have any trouble with him after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your mother ever say to you when you were a child and were naughty - I'll call a policeman - that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - no I can't exactly remember her doing that but I'll tell you what and incident happened one time and my father was very friendly with one of the policemen 
and - he had to go down from where we lived to the police station to see this friend of his and - I was a little boy in petticoats, I can remember that. Yes. And he took me down with him and when we went into the police station this policeman comes and hi
s
 uniform and he frightened me you see. I was afraid of a policeman, I don't know why but oh I was proper afraid and I cried - and I remember that as plain as anything. My father, after he'd done the business with the policeman he took me back home and he 
didn't hit me hard but he gave me a pat and said, don't you cry at a policeman again - I can remember - remember that. And my mother said, oh you shouldn't hit him for that. I remember hearing that, yes. I remember that I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was your home rented in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Rock Hill{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
The house - the house that we went to first in Rock Hill before we went - I told you we went to Chapelhouse. Yes. We rented - the house at first was rented and - then when we got back to the other house that house was supposed eventually t
o be my father's. We - my father paid into the firm a very small rent but - as it happened it never came to my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And it belonged to the firm then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh it belonged to the firm, yes. It went to the firm you see but it should have been one of 
the - things that should have come to the firm to my father you see and each of the members should have some parts of the - of the property then. But it - as it happened it didn't come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
I don't think they had a real struggle but I can remember my mother saying well my word the money doesn't go very far these days. I can remember her saying that but I - I don't think they had a struggle. I can't ever remember - going witho
ut very much. That - that is within reason according to our standard of living.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were you ever given lessons at home by your parents or anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No. We got a very good teacher and he used to - when I was in some of - the higher class then - h
e - he used to take us in subjects I don't think he was - obliged to but he used to take us in subjects like astronomy and - he'd say perhaps when it had been a clear night the night before when we got back to school, did you see so and so and so and so? 
And if you hadn't been looking he used to just tell you off a bit. And - we - I think they came in the school work, we did algebra and we used to do fractions and double fractions and all that sort of work. Parsing and analysing - in grammar and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I think I was about - five. I think I was five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 That was the Church of England school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, in that - place I showed you, yes. And then you see when the other schools were built - it was called t
he British School and - we - my father sent me there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How old were you then when you went to the British school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I should think I was six - yes. And I remember there was a teacher - a lady teacher named Turner and - I was - left handed s
o I used to - I was proper }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 left-handed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 . I think really it was hereditary because my uncle - one of my uncle's was }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 left-handed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  and - I think it went in - the family generally. Not my father, my father wasn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 left-handed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 . And my father told my teacher to correct me every time I was using the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 left hand
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  and - so she used to make me write with the right hand. Well you see when I was with myself I used to use my left hand so I can use both now - I can use both hands now you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you started school what time of the morning did you have to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Nine o'clock - nine o'clock. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}Nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you go home for your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Went home at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}twelve o'clock{\*\xmlclose} - yes. Had to walk home or run home you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And then back in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 14}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}Two o'clock{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did the boys and girls mix in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}British{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} or were you in separate halves of the building?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - in the - in the little infants school the boys and girls mixed together. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 But when we were - what age would that be - when - we were passed on later on to the other school where it was either a girl's school or a boy's school. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
My - my father was a craftsman - he was a little bit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 bigoted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
. He was a type of man who - if he - was giving anything away to anyone he always liked to give the best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 That's a nice characteristic isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. He - and - he liked to help people if he could. And my - my mother was - that way inclined to. Yes. And - she was - my mother was very sensitive over things you see and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - well if things didn't seem to - well be nice then or - or she thought she was going to offend people or anything like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 It worried her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you had a birthday you said you might have a little party in the sitting room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Oh - oh yes. Well we - well we got some of our friends the same age - practically the same age as ourselves and of course they'd bring us little presents and of course they weren't costly presents, they - just a little prese
nt you see. And - we'd have say a - a - well a special tea or something like that and perhaps a few games - various games like childish games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would relations and older people come as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well perhaps - one or two of the parents of the children you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But not family - aunts and uncles and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Not very much, no. At Christmas times, of course, later Christmas time we used to get bigger parties at Christmastime and - say birthday times but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What do you mean by later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well when I - when I got a bit older - you see, perhaps you'd have some of the - relatives, the older relatives come and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You mean when you were about twenty or older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Before the war or after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 That was before the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 On Christmas Day when you were a child did relatives come then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - I - either we went out to some of the relatives or some of the relatives came to us. And of course - we - used to hang our stockings up and - used to be de
lighted like every other child with the things that we used to get and - we used to get some fairly decent presents. I was always very fond of those lead soldiers. And I remember how delighted I was when I woke up on the Christmas morning and found a grea
t big box of these lead soldiers stuck in my stocking. Well, not my stocking, I used to have my mother's stocking. And - that - that reminds me of a - it doesn't matter now - this - going on here. My - brother-in-law had got a daughter and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Is this after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes - this was after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you went out visiting on Christmas Day would it be a big family party you'd go to or just calling in on people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - it was a big family party when I went to my grandfathers and there were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 That was your father's father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. Yes. That was - and all the all the aunts and the uncles and cousins there and there were - I can't tell you the number really altogether but quite a number of us, and we younger ones we used to have all sorts of ga
mes you see and the others used to sit round and talk and I always remember - that at Christmas times - each Christmastime that we went to grandfather's - there was an Uncle of mine, Uncle Frank I told you about, they always wanted him to sing the Farmers
 Boy. And he used to sing that old - song the Farmer's Boy and - that was one -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How does that go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Now wait a minute - I can't just remember the words. Like that. To be a farmer's boy - to be reap and to sow and to reap and to mow and to be a farmer's boy, and to be a farmer's boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Were there other occasions when you went visiting besides Christmas?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - I used to go to some cousins to their birthdays sometimes and - of course they were only little affairs you see and you didn't get all the niceties the same as you would today. But shill we used to enjoy it and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were you taken out visiting with your parents to see relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well sometimes but - that was a relation lived out in the country at a place called Bellsford and so
metimes my father - used to like to take my sister and me, we'd go out for a walk. That was rather a long walk you see and - it was - on nice day we used to enjoy it. Of course people used to do more walking in those days - than they do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would that be a weekend day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
In fact, talking about walking. I've known a time when a tradesman has perhaps taken a - a bag of tools on his back three miles - to work, to do a job and carry it on his back. And of course in those days they'd - a man was pret
ty lucky if he got a bicycle, you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, I had a bicycle, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When did you get your first one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I should think I was somewhere about - between eighteen and twenty. And - a friend of mine who used to go
 out cycling quite a bit and I remember we cycled one - August Bank Holiday - or rather, on the Saturday we started out and we cycled from Chipping Norton down to Leamington to a sister of his and we stayed - over the Bank Holiday and - we had quite a goo
d time down at Leamington. We went in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Jefferson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 {\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Gardens{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and went in the swimming bath there. I - I don't think it's the same now - I think that's been altered. I haven't been to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Leamington{\*\xmlclose} for quite a time really. And - then sometimes we'd go out variou
s parts to - have a look at an old castle or something like that. Anything that was interesting. And - go down and look at some of the old churches round about and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What day of the week would you usually go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Generally Saturdays. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You didn't have to work on Saturday then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - we didn't work in the afternoons. You worked up until {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour
}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}twelve o'clock{\*\xmlclose} and then you - you had the rest off. Before - before that you see, before my time they worked right up 'til {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} Saturday. And I r
emember there was - at my grandfather's place, some of the men, they had what they called a round robin one time. And a round robin you see is a - it - it's made like a circle and there's spaces put in the robin so that when anybody signs nobody know who 
put the first - name down first you see. They had this round robin - asking that they should have - Saturday afternoon off, you see, things like that used to happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What did he say then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well it - it - it - eventually grandfather -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Conceded it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But that was before your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes, that before my time. Yes. But they used to work up - in the - full time, what they called the full time working - when there was plenty of work about - they used to work from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour
}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning until half past vive at night, you - see, that was during my time. And - you'd start at six and work until 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
, you'd have half an hour for breakfast - you had to go from the shop to your home and get your breakfast, see. Unless you did take it of course. Then - broke off at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}
{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}twelve o'clock{\*\xmlclose} until one for - a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal and then worked on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 till}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 17}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past five{\*\xmlclose}
. And - of course work was much harder in those days because most of it was done by hand. Yes. Yes. Even the planning up you see, plan
ning hard wood and all that sort of thing and cutting generally and - all was done by hand, in those days. Except on the very big firms who'd got the machines probably in the bigger towns.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Can you tell me about Sundays - did you have different clothes on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13305173  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - as a rule we did yes. We used to have what we called a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
Sunday best}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  and then we had a - a - well perhaps a little inferior - one for when you went out to meetings at night. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
You see, some of us of course some - some people who were poor wore the same clothes nearly all the time you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Your parents attended the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Baptist{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. They were Baptists, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Your mother didn't go on with the Methodists then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not my mother - my wife. Yes, yes,. Yes. 
My mother was a Baptist from the time her - I don't know what she was before - I was born but she were a Baptist during the time I was about ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did she go to church regularly or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Pretty regularly, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 On - on - Sundays we - she - they use
d to put a - a meal over the edge of the grate you see so that there was a cooked meal when we got home from chapel. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
They used to do that you see. And - of course - my mother - wanted to be baptised to be a member of the church and - they got the baptister
y ready and - when it came to her turn to be baptised - she couldn't face the water - she got half way in the water and it took her breath away. And she couldn't go through with the service but they said they - allowed her to become a member because she t
ried, you see. And - there were a number of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You have to be totally immersed to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. You see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When were you baptised - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Wait a minute. I was baptised in 19 - now what would it be - I was eighteen. Yes. Now I was born in 1890. That - yes, that would be -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 About 1908?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. And there was - excuse me - there were seven baptised when I was baptised and we - it was a lovely service, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your father attend regularly at the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Fairly regular
ly, yes. And my grandfather, they got the - they used to have what they called their own seats there. They used to pay like a little rent, you see, and that - that went towards the fund - the fund of the chapel. You see, you had to realize that the upkeep
 of the chapel is absolutely by voluntary - collections, you see, and - and the various things they get up for - concerts and things like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you go to services when you were a boy as well as Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Yes. You see, the
 Sunday - the - there was the morning service, then the Sunday - there was a morning Sunday school before the service for the younger people. And then there was the afternoon - Sunday school and then the evening service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Which of those did you go to when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I went to most of them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 both}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  the Sunday schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. Yes, when I was a boy you see, and - see they - used to divide the afternoon Sunday school up into classes. First of all they'd have the general - opening service
 you see. And then after a hymn or two - about two hymns - you went into your classes. And then - they used to - get you on the various lessons. The - they worked the lessons on the international Bible Reading Associations lessons. And then the scholars, 
you see, if they wanted to, they could go certain evenings and - have a special tuition to go through an examination - scripture examination.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Did you do that?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I didn't do it, no. But - quite a number did. My wife - she did and she had - she came 
out in the senior part. Now that was in the Primitive Methodist though - in the senior part she came out - with some honours. I've got a book that belonged - that was given to her for - have you got time to see it. No, no, don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were you in the choir at the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. I was in the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You were telling me there was a temperance choir - was that attached to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes, and we used to sit separately up in a - in a - a big gallery in front of the organ facing the congregat
ion. And - well used to have some real good music. And when we first started I was a young chap about seventeen I should think, when I first started, and - I went on the bass side. And after I'd been there a while - the conductor said, ah, you know Ted, y
ou - you'd better go over on that tenor }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 side}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
, he said, I think you - you'd have a better tenor voice than a bass. So - of course I went over on the tenor side where I - well I've been singing tenor ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was this temperance club the Band of Hope or was it something else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. Not - not the Band of Hope. The temperance choir was - one that was got up by all people who }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 believed in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  total }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 abstinence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 you - see - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 teetotaler}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 teetotalers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were they all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Baptists}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No that was a mixture of people, the temperance choir. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So the temperance choir didn't sing in the Baptists church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Some did and some - no, not the temperance choir as a temperance choir. The Baptist choir was a separate choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were you in that too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I was in that yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
The Band of Hope was a - well it was a - a kind of - the idea was to try and - instill into the minds of youngsters that it was a better thing to be a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 teetotaler}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  then than to be getting drunk. Because in those days you know - late at night, it was terrible sometimes coming - when they were turning people out of the public houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember seeing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, ooh it was very often people were coming out and they were fighting you k
now, and - and - there was a saying, well what did you have last night? Did you have fighting or singing? The - the fighting beer or the singing beer you see. Of course beer then was only about a penny a pint you see. And, of course - but then of course t
he proportion of - according to the value of money wasn't all that different. In fact there were a lot of things that we couldn't get in those days - and wouldn't have afforded to have got like they - people do today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh - not always. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
Now in my grandfather's family the did you see and - no, we didn't do that sort of thing like some families did.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you do it on occasions or never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh sometimes. Yes. Oh - in the early days they - we used to - say
 - say that little bit - we thank you for - for all the food and all that sort of thing you know. Used to say that. In - in my early days and - my grandfather of course - my fathers father he used to reckon to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were you taught to say prayers at night when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. Oh yes. Yes, when I was a very little child - I can remember - that - the early prayer, and I was ever such a little child and I would get out - I can remember it - it was that - Gentle Jesus meek and mild, look up
on that little child, pity my simplicity - you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I think you said your parents thought it wrong to work on play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes. They - they - the - not play. Not to do things - to work, say as for going on the garden or anything of
 that on Sunday - ooh that would be a terrible thing. And - they didn't reckon to - if there was any - any buttons needed sewing on they reckoned to get that all done by the Saturday evening you see. And - various things like that they thought it was wron
g to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But you were allowed to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh you could play, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you have games like draughts and snakes and ladders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh not that sort of thing. No. No, played about you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But did you have games like that in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Used to play - my father was a very good draught player and I can -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And would he play that on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No - not on Sunday. He used to play sometimes with me and - my sister didn't care for it very much but - him and his brothers were real
ly very clever draught players because I could - never beat father as a boy you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 He used to play draughts with you then as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. I - I did - did start to - try and learn chess but I gave up - I got fed up with it somehow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was he a chess player too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - no, he wasn't a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 chess player}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 . There were two - an uncle of mine - two of my uncles, they - were men who - they used to have a saying, they could read the board. They knew practically every - every move of the - of the draugh
ts. Did I say chess. No draughts. And - when those two played each other that was a game indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not family prayers - no. Yes, just the individual prayers. We thought - saying prayers you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Did your father take an interest in politics?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Oh he was a radical. Proper radical, yes. Oh yes, he was a proper radical my father and - so were my uncles. I remember -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you know what your grandfather's views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - I don't think he troub
led a lot about politics. But my - my father was a proper radical and so was an uncle of mine - my Uncle Reuben, I was apprenticed under and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Why do you think he was a radical - do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - I - I've no idea. He - they were - followers of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
Gladstone{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and his policies and - the Liberal - way of life generally. I can't tell you why but that's what they - that was the atmosphere that I was brought up in. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would they discuss politics then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh, they were proper; they used to be h
ot headed with politics. I remember there used to be a doctor who was our family doctor - Doctor O'Kelly. He used to come up in the carpenters shop sometimes for - for things. They were - my uncle and him, they were - - they were very friendly but they we
r
e - he was a Tory - the doctor was a Tory you see and they used to go hammer and tongs at this - these politics. The doctor used to - spit almost - sometimes. My uncle was a pretty good speaker for policies you know and - he was - a man who pushed on thin
gs and - as a matter of fact, I'm going away a little bit from the - what we're talking about - he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You were saying your Uncle Reuben was the first working man there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, he was the first working man there, yes, and his name up on the board in 
the Town Hall there and - it's rather remarkable you know when - during the time he was Mayor - he used to have people come to him for help who earned more money than he earned. Remarkable you know. But he was a very able man and beside being the Mayor of
 
Chipping Norton the time he was the Mayor of Chipping Norton he was the President of the Courts - he was the head man of the Sons of Temperance - Society and used to go to the National - National part of the society, he was - he got right up in the chair 
of the National - head of the society. He was a Deacon at the chapel - Baptist chapel, now what else was he. He used to do no end of works like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 He was the uncle you were apprenticed under wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, he was the uncle I was apprenticed under.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was he a good man to learn the trade from do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Oh yes. He was a good tradesman - very good tradesman, yes. And - he was - very blunt. - Said what he thought you know. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 And - didn't mince matters, if - if he thought them.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 If he thought a bit of work wasn't properly done you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes, or - or if he was - having a - a discussion - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember your father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh - he always voted Liberal. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What about your mother - do you know what her views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - I think she more or less followed father but I don't think she troubled much about politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember her voting - she would have had the vote in 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Ah now I can't remember her voting, no. No, I can't remember her voting, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was your father a member of the Liberal party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not actually a member.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember him working for the Liberal party at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - he - he'd go round and - not working officially but he'd go round and put a word here and there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What about between elections, at other times, was he talking and working for the party then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes, he always - he was always a Liberal. The -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 He'd try and convince people would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh - yes, if - if they got talking politics. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What about you went you got older - were you in the same tradition he was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well I - I more or less followed the family traditions you know and - I suppose the atmosphere - li
ke most young people - do. I - I did that - I followed more or less in the same tradition you see, but - later on as - well I - I got a bit more open mind now you see and - did later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you ever work for the Liberal party before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well 
- I did - go at one - at the election - was that 1910 - 1910. They got me to go and help in the Liberal club. And - I did just a little bit of help but - not to actually work in the true sense of the term.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not getting the people to the poll and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was your father a member of the Liberal club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well I don't know that he was a member of the club - I don't think he was a member of the club you see, but he was a very enthusiastic Liberal. I don't think he was a member of the club, I can't remember him going to the club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember if he ever took part in any sport or went to the races or anything like that - your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No. Not - we'd got to - say sometimes we used to have some sports at - the
se holiday times and - well, he'd go to football. We used to have football - fairly regularly. There was a team called the Chipping Norton Swifts. They were a very good football team - and we used to have - most weeks - weekends, Saturdays - well the foot
b
all matches you - see and - I remember a - a pushball team coming from Oxford and - I can't tell you which year it was and - the - it was the first introduction of the big pushball - have you ever seen pushball? Well it's a great big ball - I should think
 
it's five feet in diameter. And then you see in - instead of kicking the ball they have to push it. One team is pushing against the other and - of course I don't know the rules and regulations of it but - I - I remember there was a proper row over this an
d they got to fighting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your mother go to these things too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. Not - not to - not to foot ball matches. She'd go to - to the various socials and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your mother or father belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Well - they used to - there used to be a club you could pay in the Courts. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But otherwise I don't think they belonged to anything. Not of that description.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 They didn't belong to a six fund or a funeral club or anything of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - a club, a friendly
 society. My father belonged to the Sons of Temperance. And you see if you joined that you were supposed to be a proper }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 teetotaler}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  you see and - while I'm myself am not narrow minded but I - I've been brought up as a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 teetotaler}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  and I still retain that way 
of life but - you see, from that club you used to get, if you were sick, you used to get pay and - when a person died you see there was so much funeral benefit. And - so people paid in like that in that sort of thing. Yes. There used to be Oddfellows you 
s
ee and - other friendly societies and all that sort of thing. But that was the one that my father joined and he put me in - in what they called the cadets so that if - if I - happened to be sick as a schoolboy you see there was so much allowed for doctor 
and everything else you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Can you tell me about this Co-op club - was that the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 dividend}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - there - the dividend came back from what you paid in as capital. You see, you - you - it was kind of a bank. They still do that now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What sort of a savings club was the one they belonged to at the Co-op?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well that - they - they still have a - a kind of a club - it's a - and you pay so much in and then you get the - value of that every Christmastime. You see you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your mother get clothes - was it for clothing or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
You could get anything - anything with - well with what you're - according to what you paid in you see. Now, at the present time you see, you pay - I pay in a club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you were a child how did you get on with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - we used to get on all right but my sister used to play pranks and of course naturally - naturally there were little - little squabbles occasionally. Not - we used to get on all right together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you play together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. Yes. But as - as she got older we didn't play together very much. She used to go with her friends and I used to go with mine you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you play with the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 neighbours'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  children or did your friends come from further away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 W
ell - you see when I was living at Rockhill the - there were all - the children up all around. We used to have games all together. It didn't - it didn't matter who they were you see, if they were up in the district we used to play together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you play in the yard or in the street or in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well it was - you saw Rockhill didn't you? Well we used to play around there you see, out - well you'd call it in the street wouldn't you. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you ever play in the homes of the other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - I used to go to my cousins and did I tell you that I used to go there sometimes and my - his father belonged to a band, did I tell you that? No, well you see, I used to go and play with my cousin sometimes. They lived just up above where I lived. }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
And - we - used to have all sorts of games in the house, that was if it was bad weather and - of course his sisters - he'd got sisters and we used to play together you see and - one thing I used to be very fond of and that was - when sometimes when 
we got there and were playing - we had to stop playing because my cousins father, he used to play a harp and his grandfather - my cousins grandfather used to come up to play a violin and an old man named Bridges used - he played a violin and they used to 
- practice for a dance band. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And we used to like to sit there and listen to this - music that they were practicing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 That must have been very nice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 My cousin's father could play a harp very well indeed. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were there any children t
hat your parents forbad you to play with or disapproved of you playing with or did they not mind who you played with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well they didn't mind who I played with as long as they - they didn't like me to play with - children who used bad language. And - p
eople if they were too scruffy - if the boy was too scruffy you see they didn't like me to play with them. Of course there were quite a number of scruffy children about then - children with their goes sticking out of their boots and they were in rags and 
- dirty too. And - but - as a - as a rule most of the tradesmen's children, they were pretty decent. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What were the occupations of most of the families up in Rockhill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What - do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were they mostly tradesmen or labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 W
ell - they were a - a mixture of different people. One man who lived up above - us, he was a postman - and - there was another was - who lived above us - was a plumber. And there was one old lady had a - a little shop up there. And some of them were labou
rers - farm labourers higher up. They were varied in - different types of work they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would they vary too in the different standard of living do you thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Oh yes. Now a little higher up still there was a - a sweep. And - this sweep an
d his sons used to - have a fairly big business for sweeping. Now they used to - every so often they used to get - all the farmers used to come with their horses and the big wagons, you know the wagons that they used to cart the hay about in, with the fou
r
 wheels and the big wheel behind and the little wheel in front like the big racks, and they used to - get all the soot bags and fill these wagons up with the soot bags and - you'd see perhaps one or one or two of them riding on top of these soot bags with
 their faces all black you know, covered with soot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Well - my mother didn't like me to get dirty but she - she didn't make a lot of fuss - as long as I didn't spoil my clothes, you see, th
at - I remember having a good hiding - my mother gave me a good hiding one time because I'd put a new pair of trousers on and of course they were short trousers for boys then and - I'd been climbing over while we were playing with a cousin, climbing over 
some barbed wire. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And - I'd only had those trousers on in the morning you see and - I ripped a great big in - with this barbed wire and - my mother gave me a good hiding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How did you feel about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh I didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You also used to go bicycling but that was when you were about eighteen or twenty years old wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - before that time - my father brought home a - an old lady's bicycle. And - it wasn't really a - an exceptionally good bicycle but - I used to - I learned to rid
e by getting on it and - letting my legs dangle and go down hill and then - you see - you saw that place between those two houses, one of my grandfather's and one of his brother's - in between - I used to come down between there - that old - the hill ther
e you see and that went up to the back of the place we lived in when we came back from Chapelhouse. And - that's how I learned to ride. I - I remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you ride the lady's bike round the town and all that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not - not on that, no. But eventual
ly - I got - got on my father's bicycle. He allowed me to get on when I could ride and occasionally you see. And - I remember - remember one time I was riding - not that bicycle - my - my father's bicycle and somehow or other I couldn't guide that just wh
ere I wanted to go and run into a man. Oh he was vicious he was. If you'd have seen the vicious look on his face when he - when he looked at me - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What other ways did you spend your time as a schoolboy - did you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No. I used to be - I used to play with those lead soldiers quite a lot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What about sport - did you play football or did you just go and watch it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No, I didn't play - didn't play football or - or sports of that sort. I did mainly gymnastic work and physical t
raining and - I don't know whether you'd call it a sport but I used to - go round running round you know, do long distance running and - we - I suppose you'd call that a sport of course - we had a harriers club and - one time - did I show you a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 photo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  of that? Went out as a - hares another man and myself and we got - oh half an hour before the - before the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 hounds}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 got back. And we went a matter of ten miles then I should think. And - things like that I was interested in. And - I was interested in - in the gymnasium I used to do boxing and wrestling - general gymnastics - gymnastic work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 That's the one you showed me down opposite the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. No, not that one. That - that was another one, that's along High Street, we didn't go along there not rea
lly. It - it was a place, you went up a passage and it was - a kind of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 a hall}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 at the back there, rather a big place and all the gymnastic stuff was in there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Can you tell me how you first got interested in gymnastics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - really and t
ruly - we used to - at school used to do all sorts of - games there at - at the school as a schoolboy and - then I used to read about some of these strong men. And - so I - gradually took an interest in - in - in things to do with physical training.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Where did you read about these strong men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well I read in a boys paper called The Boy's Friend first of all there was the Great Sando, he got some articles there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You've got some books of his haven't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, yes. But he got these articles
 in this Boy's Friend and - I started reading that and - then I started to take an interest in it and then a friend of mine - through a friend of mine I got those big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 dumbbells}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 . I went in for the - went in for the Sando - you saw the dum - did you see those }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 dumbbells}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  - I went in for the Sando system. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you teach yourself or was it through this friend that you learnt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh I - I taught - taught myself at first - from the - from a magazine called the Health and Strength Magazine that use
d to come out every week. There's some wonderful articles there. And then eventually there was a man named Thomas Inch who used to write articles on weight lifting and I was somehow attracted to weight lifting - and I read this and then I tried this, I ha
d some old - weights, some rough old weights and started training. And eventually I got some proper weights and then went in for it properly you see with -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 This was while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No, just after I'd left school that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was there a weight lifting club then in Chipping Norton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
Not when I started but eventually there was a club and - I went down to the club and there wasn't a proper teacher of weight lifting but there was a very good man named Bignall who - was a pretty 
good gymnast and we used to go for - through gymnastics there but - there was a very good trainer at the Chipping Norton gymnasium I spoke to you about just before now and - his name's Slade and he used to put us through some pretty good gymnastic work on
 
parallel bars and the rings and horizontal bars and - the - the ladder for you know, swinging along on the ladder and - we used to do wrestling, fencing with the foils and - single sticks and I was no good at all at single sticks because I was very good a
t a foil, if I can say that, and - I used to enjoy going to those meetings like that.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was that after work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 That was after work then at that gymnasium, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 enter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  for competitions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No, no real competitions. The 
only - I tried - in weight lifting I tried for - some Health and Strength certificates you - I showed you those did I. Yes. But I never went in for proper competitions. But I used to give - give displays at -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Tell me about those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well you saw the picture?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Of the Hospital fetes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. Well - my first display I gave in Chipping Norton was after the first great war - but I'd been giving displays along with two or three others in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}India{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} through - various places in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}India{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And - some - mainly 
gymnastic and strong man business, you see, assisted by these others and the others were very good - very good - at gymnastics and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Before the first world war did you ever demonstrate at a fair or a fete at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes, that - that was before - yes - before the first great war. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 1914 war you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You used to demonstrate then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Well - and my first demonstration and - was at - in a field - I think that was a temperance fete and I
 gave a demonstration of strength there. That was my first demonstration that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How old would you have been then, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I should be about - twenty. Twenty then. And - I remember - when I got on platform I'd got some weights and - up on
 the platform and I got my coat on you see and - I heard a proper - ooh - when I pulled my coat off and they saw my arm muscles. I - I remember that quite definitely. And then a man came on to lift the weight and he - he - he struggled like anything and h
e couldn't get it much above his knees - the weight that I was able to put above my head one hand you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How long did your demonstration go on for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Somewhere about half an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Just you or were there others demonstrating as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 My first was just me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did people have to pay to watch you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh no, it was at a fete you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 One of the attractions at a fete?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What did your mother and father and family think about your weight lifting and all that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - my - my mother, she - she didn't seem to trouble much one way or the other. And my - my father, he didn't say a lot. But after a while when he found that I was gradually developing strength I think he was rather interested.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you enjoy demonstrations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Yes, I enjoyed - well - perhaps I was a little bit egoistic. At any rate I used to like to do that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you have close friends who also did it - people who were in that little discussion club you had, were they also in weight lifting?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - with regard to the - do you mean the discussions of generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You have a photograph of a group of you who used to have discussions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh - ah, no, that was on any subject you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were they also interested in weigh lifting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Some were and some weren't. They - they didn't do weight lifting - those that were on that photograph - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was the weight lifting your main interest in the years after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well it was - that and gymnastics generally, running - and running and all that sort of thing. You see, my idea was that }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 I\rquote m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 - I liked to feel that I could - jump over something if I'd got to or if I - I could run if - away from something if I'd got to, or I could get somewhere quick if I wanted to
, you see, or if - if I've got to lose something out of my way that I - have the strength to do it and - if I could defend myself if anybody started knocking me about you see. That - that was my main interest in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were you ever paid for demonstrating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
No. No. I - I was paid - I was paid for doing physiotherapy. Well you see in - in doing physiotherapy you see you have to give exercises and consequently when I tried to - lift - and tried for some record in lifting I had to lift - they wouldn't
 allow me to lift as an amateur, you see, because I'd received money for physiotherapy you see. You see, they'd - they were right - right particular about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 In your running, did you compete against other places there in your harriers club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 W
ell - only just to - not to really compete but to see what we could do - to see - see - how we could stand up against something. See the - the harriers when we used to go perhaps for a - a six mile run or a - go for a - a four mile run - just a matter of 
doing it to see whether we could do it you see. And to see how we could stand it and - also with an idea of being beneficial from - the - the exercise standpoint.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you go to any theatres or concerts as a lad in Chipping Norton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you mean to 
listen to - oh yes. Yes. Used to go to concerts. I used to love going to concerts and - I used to love going to concerts where there was - a choirs and where there was harmony - where the singing was nice and harmonious and - I used to like to hear - inst
rumental music and also solos. I used to love to hear people who'd got nice voices sing a solo.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What about the theatre - were there ever any plays performed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well you see the - we - in Chipping Norton - didn't get much chance to go to a theatre y
ou see, you didn't travel in those days the same as people do today but - I used to like to go to a theatre, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was there an amateur dramatic club or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not in my time. No, not in those early days. But we used - I - used to - 
as I told you, belonged to a choir and we used to go out - five - giving concerts and I used to take part in - solos - tenor solos you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What about the cinema - that started before the war didn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. The cinema started at the Odd fellow
s Hall in chipping Norton and - they used - they were the old silent pictures and there used to be a - a lady used to play the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 piano}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  while the picture was being shown. You see, the pictures used to come on and then it was - all printed on, what was happening and all to give you the story and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you go along to see those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Oh yes, I - and - I used to like to see Charlie Chaplin. We used to be very fond of seeing Charlie Chaplin. But I also liked drama. I liked to see a good drama too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
But in the way of theatres do you ever remember travelling companies coming and putting plays on or anything like that - going to see plays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - we'd go to - on one or two occasions go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Oxford
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} or - you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But they didn't come to Chipping Norton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Oh - ah, now, yes, some of them - there used to be some very small tented theatres used to come, well I didn't go to those because I didn't think they were all that good really and - I forget what you paid to go, I think you 
paid for - about sixpence to go in. It was a tent kind of thing they put up and they'd perhaps stay for a week, the company, and I didn't go to those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you were a schoolboy did you have any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. It was only matter of a few pence though. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was it regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes, but - nothing - no - nothing set, you see, you asked your mother for it - for some money, you see, if you could have some money then she'd perhaps give you tuppence or something like that. Now you see you 
could get a lot of sweets for a penny. You - you could get quite a lot of - well you could get a farthings worth of sweets. You could go and buy a farthings worth of sweets. Then - at that time you could get - did I tell you - twenty-two eggs for a shilli
ng. And twenty-four oranges for a shilling you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You told me that your mother didn't pay anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did anybody unpaid come in ever to give her a hand with her housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No, she never had anybody - she
 - she did all the housework and - didn't need anybody you see, and of course I think I told you I used to - clean the knives and forks and my father's shoes - boots and my mother's shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So she had help from you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember her having an illness while you were at Rockhill and having anyone looking after her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - not - not real illness. She didn't have anyone to look after her but it - it was an illness in a sense because she used to get a hit depressed sometimes, yes, she - she got run down like that occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So she couldn't do very much you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 That's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did a relation come in and help her at all then or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well she - she wasn't in a state that she required help like that. N
o - no, the - she didn't require that, then of course if - anything needed doing when I was some - where about twelve years of age I used to be able to do quite - know a bit you see. And I remember one of my delights was to - on a winter's morning to get 
up silently and - and get a fire lit and then see the look of pleasure on her face when she came down to - and saw the fire was all lit and it was nice and warm. I used to like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You liked doing things for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Well I - I liked d
oing - I like doing things for people - what I like to see, if you do something for somebody then you see that look of pleasure on their face. I like doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would you say that your parents had friends when you were a young boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. We had 
quite a number of friends, they used to come in and - relatives used to come in then. Yes. Oh we used to get plenty of company
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would you say that your parents shared the friends - or was it just your father's friends or your mother's friends or did th
ey have the same friends in common?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well I don't - I don't know that they - they seemed the friends and that was it - they used to come -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Friends of both of them you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were they couples and single people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Sometimes
 couples and - yes. Sometimes single people. See. There were some like that but there were also the couples that used to come and perhaps one friend who was a friend of both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And some as you say were particularly your mother's friends and some particularly your father's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. There were some, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When they came into the house was it by invitation or did they just drop in casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - both. Sometimes by }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 invitation,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  sometimes by - just in a casual way. You see, perhaps - perhaps my 
mother would say to some - well come to tea or something like that you see. Then - then of course in those - those days we used to have - suppers. Every Sunday night when we came out of chapel there was a cousin of my father's used to come up every Sunday
 night for quite a period. Then we used to have a - all sorts of things for supper - meat and tart and all - all the things, well I shouldn't want it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What sort of time would you have that supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh somewhere about - anywhere between eight and {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}
{\xmlattrvalue 9}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
. You come out of the chapel and you - they'd come up and - be with us and we'd have a jolly good sing, see both my sister and I could play the piano and - my father used to sing bass and I used to sing tenor. My sister contralto and my moth
er - soprano. And then these others would sing whatever they - could sing. Sometimes used to have a proper sing, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Must have been lovely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did friends come also for tea and supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not many. Now and then there - th
ere would be a friend come but it was generally relatives used to come then - and that was a relative of my father's used to come pretty well every Sunday for quite a period. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 If a person called in unexpectedly would they be offered something to eat and drink or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes, yes - that is - anyone you'd know. Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When your mother asked somebody to tea was that to tea as a meal or just a cup of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh - a meal. Yes. But - it was generally bread and butter and cake and -
 some; thing like that you see and tea - tea drink and - perhaps jam and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not anything cooked or meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 That was for supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were people invited for {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well we used to have - call it dinner you see not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
No. And we used to have a good cooked dinner, vegetables and meat and generally - some pudding or tart - jam tart or apple tart or something like that to finish up you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you invite people to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So you saw quite a lot of people - it was a sociable sort of household?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your parents go to people for supper too and meals and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Sometimes - not very often. Sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did neighbours call in and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - not exactly to supper or anything like that, the - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 next-door}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  neighbours but they - they used - if there was any help needed, you know, I mean not to come and do a lot of work or anything like that but -
 if there was any help needed they'd come and help you see, well we used to do the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What kind of thing for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - perhaps there was - say perhaps there might be some job you got in a bit of a fix and they'd come and give o hand or 
something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Handiwork and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Or anything like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When your parents got together with their friends and family they used to have these singing and musical evenings didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did they ever play any games together of any kind do you think?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - I can't remember any friends coming in to play games but - my father and I used to play draughts and things like that you see.;

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And your uncles were very good at draughts weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Some people divide society into different social classes you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 At that time when you were a child how did you thing the social classes were then in Chipping Norton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Well you see - a person who - who
 person who earned two pound a week when I was a little - a boy, was supposed to be a proper gentleman, you see - the - a person who earned the tradesman's wage of anywhere about twenty five shillings or - or a bit more or a bit less, well you were just l
ooked upon at the ordinary artisan, you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well then, of course, farm }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 labourers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 labourers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 generally, they was looked upon as just a bit inferior. There were the real distinctions and a man who was - well, who was really m on - a moneyed man, ooh, he
 was some lord, you see. He was a - you were supposed to have a finger go to the forelock and all that sort of thing you see. Well - there was a vast difference in those days - say people with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173  plenty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  of money wouldn't want to mix to make a companion of - a
nyone who was of a lower order according to their - their ideas of - of order then. And there was all - that - that vast difference in the - social position. You see - people who - the poorer people of course they - very often were reckoned to today to th
e - person with money. Now there was an instance - you know the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Hawkins}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  I told you about where that tomb was in the church?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 The old lords of the manor you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes - oh the - when I was a little boy of course I didn't get this experience I was i
n Chipping Norton, but - my wife's father lived up in Over Norton and most of the houses belonged to the Dawkins people, it was an estate you see. But my wife's father - didn't work for Dawkins people, it was an estate you see. But my wife's father - didn
'
t work for Dawkins. He worked in - at the mill - down at the mill. He was in - doing the dye work you see. And he rented a house up there you see. Well now this - the old Lady Dawkins, she used to go round and - and - well, give advice here and there to t
h
e people who were in - who worked for them, and she'd go round and pull the pot lids off to see what they was cooking in the pot lids - in the pot you see. And all things like that. And if they were having a meal at the dinner time and she went into the h
o
use - any of the houses, she expected them to sit upright like the soldier does when the officer goes round at mealtime, she expected them to do that you know. And - she went into my father-in-law's place one time and they were having a dinner. She expect
e
d them to do the same, of course they were nothing to do with her actually. And - my - my eldest - the eldest brother of my wife went on with his dinner. And the others, they sort of half sat up and - and half went on with their dinner. Well she said, oh 
you rude boy. And - ooh, said all sorts of nasty things to him and she took his plate off him. You see, she took his plate and - and put it down again and told her to go about her business. Oh, that was a terrible thing, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did she go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 We-ll - 
well I don't know really what happened but of course she began to realize that she couldn't do the same with them as with her own people, see. And - another instance that was rather remarkable. Colonel Dawkins, he was a Colonel, the - the son and eventual
l
y the estate came to him you see and he lived at the big house out at Over Norton and - he happened to put up for the Chipping Norton council and - on the election day he was going back to Over Norton and my father-in-law caught him up and - Colonel said 
to him, well Sandels I suppose you voted for me? And my father-in-law said, well Colonel, he said, I don't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 tell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 anybody who I voted for, he said, that - voting is secret, he says, I don't tell anybody who I voted for. Oh well, he said, I suppose you voted a
gainst me then? Well - he wouldn't speak to my - passed my father-in-law by after that. Wouldn't speak to him. And do you know, my father-in-law had voted for him, you see. Yes, yes. And - of course all that is - we realize - is changed now. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were you brought up to touch your hat and say Sir to certain people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - no. No, not exactly - although - although my father and mother were particular - particular about - being good mannered. Yes, they - they were particular about that but - no toadying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would you say that you were taught to speak or behave differently to any people differently from other people or treat everyone the same?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well I don't know - I mean - we were told - to be decent to people and - well, they reckoned us to behave ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Who would you call Sir at that time - would you call anyone Sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - I used to call some people Sir but - I - I felt a bit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 reluctant}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  to be too emphatic with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Who would you have called Sir when you were a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well you'd call the schoolmaster Sir. Yes. And - well you'd call someone who - who you knew who was a little bit above you in station.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What about the minister of the chapel - would you call him Sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Can you remember anybody showing respect to your father in that way, or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
No, I can't remember anyone - can't remember anyone doing that because my - my father he - he tried to teach - tried to speak decently to people you see. But there was an occasion during an el
ection when a man - hit at him - hit at my father on High Street and of course my father could use his fists a bit and he knocked him over, knocked him clean down on the pavement you see. But - my father}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173  wouldn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  stand anything - if anybody was aggressive.
 Of course, he wasn't a big man, he was - about - about the same size as myself but he - he could use his fists you see. And - but he wouldn't - he was a man who didn't like to quarrel but if anybody really got aggressive he - he was aggressive then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Who were considered the most important people in Chipping Norton at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You mean - persons actual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not the names necessarily but their sort of functions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - now - the Town Clerk }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 for one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  thing - at one time. Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 he was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  supposed to
 be - oh, quite a big man - in fact I remember - his wife used to think she could go around and do all sorts of things and the policeman ordered her off the pavement because she was standing at that corner of New Street you - see where all the traffic was
 - and that and of course she was discussing things with another person and - two or three persons, and - blocking up the pavement you see. A policeman named Hedges went and - as you see, get off the pavement. Oh, she was quite indignant about}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173  that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  and eventually the policeman was moved. The policeman was moved to another district Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Through her influence do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Through her influence yes. At least they - at least they reckoned it was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was that before the first war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - 
that was - that was how people - how those sort of people would treat anyone you see. How they expected to be treated as - well, lady so and so and so and so you see and - after all, he was only the Town Clerk, you see and - and then if - if a man was in 
a - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 tradesman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 then who was pretty prosperous he was supposed to be, oh, Mister this and that you see and - if anyone answered him back, well of course that was a terrible thing to do.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173  Answer}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  a man back like that you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you mean an employee of his or anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - if he was an employer, yes, or - if he'd got a good business - like some of the business places in drapery or - grocery or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember anybody ever treating you as if you were an inferior person when you were a lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes, I - some used to treat me like that. But - I - I think that was because I was always shy. I was a very shy boy. Yes, I - it may have been that and - it may have been because of - we belonged to the artisan class you see, may have
 been that. But I think it was mainly because I was a - very shy boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Can you remember the schoolteachers in the town, who they associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well they - they associated with - people who - well, were a little bit above other people in intell
ectual - standards. Because you see you - you'd get - I'm not saying that labourers - I'm not saying that none of them were intellectual but you see they didn't get the opportunities of education and consequently they couldn't discuss some of the things t
hat the other people were interested in. And naturally you see it made a kind of a calls distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Who did the farmers mix with and go around with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - it depended upon the farmer you see because they - you realize today there is a differen
ce in this - in the position of farmers. Some farmers were prosperous and some were - they had to work - work and work to get a living and - there were - you see, the difference is in the way people were educated and they - they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 seemed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  to have their - their own special cliques and classes you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
That farmer that you mentioned who had a special set in the Baptist chapel, did he mix with the other people in the chapel or did he keep himself to himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh he'd mix with the people in the chapel. Y
es. But - but you see he'd have - he'd have his special friends, you see, you realize that. He'd have his special friends which belonged to - another class then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And he had that special seat in the chapel all on his own with his family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes, he had - he had the special seat there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
When you were a lad did you or your father or any of the other people in the chapel think it was in anyway wrong that the rich man should have the special seat or did you not think of it like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well I can't remember - thinking as it mattered, you see, that - and of course, you went to chapel and they - in the chapel and in the services generally and in the other meetings that came in the week and all that sort of things, there was that social so
rt of feeling, you didn't think a lot of that you know. Oh, you felt perhaps - you felt - I used to feel that perhaps a person like that I was a little bit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 inferior}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 , you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You accepted the way things were do you think in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, well I - I felt - well, I don't know so much as that man you know, and all that sort of thing and - in - in one thing and another.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were there labouring people in the chapel too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh, some of all sorts. Yes. Some of all classes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would you say there were a different type of people went to the church and the chapel or were they much the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
You mean the Church of England? Well - there was - there were the different types there you see, there were different - different types just the same a
s at the chapel but I think there was a little bit of - difference in feelings towards each other. See - there was that little bit of antagonism from the - from the standpoint of the religious views. Yes, but Church of England and Baptists and the Methodi
sts, they had a - there was a kind of a little - religious antagonism, you see, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 that's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 been cut out in the later years. You see, people who were younger they don't realize - how - how people used to look at the other religions.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Like in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Northern Ireland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Well we didn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 we weren\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  like that. No, we weren't as bad as that but we - oh they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 There was that difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes, there was a difference. You see there was the difference in - you see, for instance now if we go out
 of the religious side of - of this - of this talk - we Baptists you see, we believed that a child - oh I told you - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And you had the cradle roll and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes. Oh I told you that did I. Well you see there were those difference
s and sometimes it was a big thing. You see, and - and the Church of England and the Methodist they - they both - agree on the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 sprinkling}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  you see, don't they. And there wasn't the quite the same antagonism but - but there was a bit. There are other differences.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did it go to the extent of not having friends of people in other religions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well, not to that extent. It depend - a great deal depended upon who the - who the friends were you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your mother and your father have the same attitudes about social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - I can't remember having much discussion about that. But - I - oh I think my father used to - he used to be a - have a liberal outlook, you see, and of course he - he had those liberal ideas but - in the Liberal movemen
t you see at that time there was the - difference of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 opinion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 as to whether a person should have so much money more than another and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a certain social class - do you think she was class conscious in a sense?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I think she was a bit class conscious. Yes. More so than my father. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What class would she have put herself in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh she - she - I think she felt that she - well, she couldn't discuss things with some peopl
e and she - she - she felt - a little bit - the underdog like that. From the standpoint of view of discussion and knowledge generally you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 She felt a bit inferior in a way did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, I think she felt a bit like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were there any particular people do you think she felt that way with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes - when - we were in the company of particular people, especially people that were - well, fairly well off then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember anybody at that time talking about somebody as a real lady 
or a real gentleman - using that phrase about people and was it generally used about people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes, there was - a person with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 plenty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  of money, oh she was a lady, you see. Or a person with - with - who - just the ordinary person it was a woman you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember at that time a distinction between craftsmen and labourers - a big distinction in the social attitude?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - you see the - the - in the - building trade a joiner was supposed to be the king of - of the building trade, you se
e. Yes, and - and then the mason - the mason well, he wasn't quite so - supposed to be quite on the same rung of the ladder then although he was a - a mason had to be a pretty good man. But the labourer, he was, well, he was just a labourer. That was it y
ou see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember some people being talked about as rough and some as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Oh yes. Oh yes. Oh yes, there were - there was - well, naturally if you - you don't see the people about now like - there used to be in my younger days. Some
 of the people were rough and especially some of those who used to go to the public house and their main idea was to - after they'd finished their work to go to the public house and stick there for hours and - drinking, then they used to get ill tempered 
a
nd they - some had to pushed out - had to be - they had to throw them out there and then they'd come out shouting and - and they'd do all sorts of haywire things. And sometimes it wasn't safe for a - a - a woman then if - late at night. When it was turnin
g }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 out }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
- ah or some of the other public houses - it wasn't safe sometimes for a - a woman or any - anybody then to go by when they were being turned out if they'd - had - that class of drink that made them ill tempered. Some used to come out singing, you see
, and some used to come out - wanting to fight everybody, you see. You see, they didn't know quite what they were doing they - it didn't matter who the person was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were there those sort of people living round you at - Rockhill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well there was a public house right up, ever such far above us and we didn't - we weren't close to a public house you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But the actual families or people, did they live near you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not close by us but there were one or two up a little higher up Rockhill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember people at that time moving from one social class to another - up or down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Not really. No I can't remember - not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you remember seeing the policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Yes, you see, the police - we saw the police station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 It was quite near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. I remember one time - oh - just - opposite - not really opposite but in the other road that's opposite the Rockhill Road where I said you went up to the Roman Catholic church, there wa
s - at one time a lodging house for tramps. Some of the tramps who could go and pay so }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 much}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 instead of going to the - tramp warder they called it. And sometimes they used to get some very rough men there, you here all sorts of rows going by - going on at n
ight you see. We could hear that going on. And I remember one time, there was a tramp, he was - oh, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 rather}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 a - bad customer and - he - I remember seeing the police and the policeman was trying to take him up - I remember seeing this policeman holding this 
man's wrist and there was a big knife in this man's - wrist you see - this man's fist. And this policeman was holding his wrist to keep this knife away from his chest and then another policeman came up and helped him and they took him into the - that was 
not very far away from that police station. Yes, I remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 seeing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 did}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 you think the police treated the people on the whole in Chipping Norton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh well they weren't too bad. No, they weren't too bad - although the - the policemen, when 
I was a boy some of them used to carry a stick with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I want to know how you felt about the teachers - we'll talk about the British school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You told me about a teacher who was very keen on astronomy - was that at that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Oh - no. That was - well it was the British school but it was the Boys British school up the - what we call the Green. You see, I was sent - that was the infants school I was at -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Where you showed me last week you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Well now, that's right - the other school was the boys}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  British school up the - what they call the Green. And of course it was all boys there naturally. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 
And the girls used to - the girl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 school - the elder girls were - the school was up above. There's two stories if you no
tice in that school in New Street and the infants was down below in the bottom rooms, and the - elder girls in - up in the upper story you see. And of course that was the girls school as well as the infants}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  school. And - ours was just simply the boys scho
ol. And - that was - when we were old enough to be transferred from that you see up - up to the school in the Green. There were the different classes there naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 About how old were you then do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Now - oh I expect I was about six or
 seven possibly. You see because these schools then, they'd been - newly built. I was somewhere about six or seven I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You didn't transfer again after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You were at that school right on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I was at that school until I was fourteen years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So you were at three schools altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So let's concentrate on that {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}British{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} because it was the same type of school except it was in a different part when you were in the juniors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What did you think of the teachers there - what did you feel about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well they were - very good. Yes, they were very good and I - I - can't ever remember having any - terrible thoughts about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you ever remember being punished for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Only we used to - sometimes if we made a mistake we'd - were - when they were asking - when the teacher was asking questions and - perhaps we - gave rather a bad answer they'd give us the cane on the hand, just across the h
and you know and - I can't ever remember being punished very severely but there was an instance that was rather - amusing. My brother-in-law - now dead - he - he was sitting in the same class as I was in and - we were getting - we were getting on towards 
being the older boys then at that time and he played }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 truant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 and his father told the teacher to deal with him, you see. So when he came - to school the next day after he'd played truant - Mr Oaks, that was the headmaster, he said, Sandels, where were you yes
terday? And of course there was a bit of an excuse and all that sort of thing. He said, well come out here lad. And the master laid him across the desk and caned in those days you know - and - oh, he did tan him on his seat. And - after the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7241175\charrsid13305173 tanning}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  he came
 - my brother-in-law came and sat by me and I said - whispered to him - George didn't that hurt? He said no. And he told me after that he knew that the teacher was going to deal with him so he went down to his grandfather's farm that evening and he - he g
ot a lot of wool and padded his seat with wool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 He deserved not to feel the pain - it was such an ingenious idea wasn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, but - no, as far as the teachers was concerned - were concerned - and as far as I was concerned - I don't - I'm not 
trying to make out I was a good boy - but as far as I'm concerned I can't think of anything that was - really nasty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6702427\charrsid13305173  at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 all. Not - not with regard to myself but - of course some of the boys needed a little bit of correction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were most of the children from similar types of home to your own or were there lots of different types?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh, there was different types, at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6702427\charrsid13305173 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  time there used to be - boys used to come from the workhouse. It was called the workhouse in those days of course. And - these boys, s
ome of them they were a little bit irresponsible and of course they had to be corrected quite a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did the workhouse boys wear different clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 They wore cordur - corduroy suits and - course they - they looked as if they belonged to a - lowe
r class then. But - of course they were clean. And we knew they belonged to the workhouse - anyone knew the people who belonged to the workhouse because the - elder people, they wore the similar corduroy clothes you see. It was a dark type of corduroy - n
ot these nice coloured corduroys that you get today. And it looked cheap and rough you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did these children keep to themselves in the school or did they mix in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. Oh no, they mixed just the same as any other - boys you see. Oh we mixed with them just the same as any other boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 They weren't left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh no, oh no, they - they - well - as far as boys were concerned they were just the same as any other boys. At the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you think the teachers discriminated against them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
No. As far as I can remember I can't remember them - discriminating in any way at all. They - they gave them the same lessons, they sat with us in - in the classes and - I remember once incident at the - there was one boy they used to call hi
m Shadder and his father was one of these old rag and bone men used to go round collecting rag and bones and - we used to call him Shadder Soul, you see, Saul was his surname and - he was a little bit unruly and one of the teachers, a young teacher, his n
ame was Gibbs and - at that time they used to call some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6702427\charrsid13305173 of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 the Gibbs people Monkey Gibbs - why I don't know. But - this teacher Gibbs,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6702427\charrsid13305173  he}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  was very decent sort of young man and - }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Shadder}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  had been misbehaving and he was sitting on the end of the seat you see 
- there - there were long seats with a desk in the front - long desks and long seats you see. And Shadder was sitting on the end and - this teacher Gibbs went and hit him. And he slipped onto the form and - he started crying, he was rubbing his eyes and h
e
 shouted out - Monkey, long tail - knock it off you see. So the teacher fetched him out in front and there was a proper scuffle with these two. And - eventually the headmaster came in and took him in - into his room and we could hear Shadder shouting out 
- he was having the stick you see. Things like that happened occasionally. I remember - two brothers named Gibbs - they - they were named Gibbs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were they in the same family or were they not related?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. They were - they were - they were some rel
ation to the teacher. This was in the headmaster's class. One brother was in the - what we called the sixth standard and - his other brother was in the seventh and somehow or other - the one in the seventh had done something, I don't know what it was, but
 the headmaster went and started tanning him across the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 shoulders}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 with the cane. And - the other brother stands up, said, let him alone, Oaks. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
You see, so that as soon as the teacher - as soon as Mr Oaks went to the other one to correct him, the other one started. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
That went on for quite a time but of course they were subdued eventually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were these workhouse boys?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No. They were - they really came from a decent family actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 This would be exceptional behaviour would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Yes. Very exceptional really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you said he shouted out Monkey ring tail - what was the other word?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Rock-a-dock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What is that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 I - I don't know what the meaning is but that's what he shouted out and that's - that's been in my memory ever since. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you say the Gibbs were called Monkey Gibbs - did lots of families have nicknames at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - some did and some didn't. But I can't remember many nicknames really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your family have a nickname?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Can you remember any others just off hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I'm afraid I can't at the moment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When did they stop being called the Monkey Gibbs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Well - I don't think - many of the - what shall I say - the better types were called that but - there was 
a - a family of Gibbs, they were very poor and one of them was a little bit inclined to be - well - not quite same then and he was in the workhouse and - he used to - well, more or less ape the monkey I suppose in the way he used to go about.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And that's how it originated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But was this teacher - related to those poor Gibbs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - somehow or other, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You said you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 would}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  be corrected for giving a wrong answer - can you ever remember anything else you were corrected for with the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - I remember one time there - a lot of little - I can't quite remember what they were - lot of little square cards and the boy named }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Absalom}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  gave me some of these cards and I put them in my pocket and - I went to put my - in school I we
nt to put my hand in my pocket to get my handkerchief I think it was, and out came some of these cards on the floor. The schoolmaster saw them drop on the floor, oh, he said, it's you is it? He said, I shouldn't have thought it'd be you. And I said - I wo
n
dered what was happening you see. And these cards had been stolen out of the - master's - schoolmaster's desk you see. So of course I - I didn't like - getting anybody into trouble but I had to tell him who gave me these cards you see. Well - well of cour
se at first before it was found out that I wasn't the thief I had a bit of a - just a little bit of caning for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And then you said afterwards that it was this other lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes. The schoolmaster apologised though when he found out that I was not the thief.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
You said the teachers didn't discriminate against the workhouse children - were there any children they singled out for extra favourable treatment in the school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - I don't know that I can remember extra favourable treatmen
t except there were - one boy I think he was a - something to do with a friend of the headmaster and - perhaps he gave him a little bit more privilege but nothing to mention much about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 Privilege}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  in what particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well it seems as if he fa
voured him - I can't exactly explain really but it seemed as if he - seemed to think a little bit more about him then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 In the way he talked to him do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 In - yes. Yes, or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did he give him extra lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No, no, nothing of that - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 More in his manner towards him you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, that's right. There's one - one experience I had in that same class - during the arithmetic period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 This is in the headmaster's class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Is that the top of the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. During the arithmetic period we used to get cards and so many sums that we had to like for our - perhaps fractions, perhaps double fractions or just the ordinary single fractions or any of those sort of sums you see. And - there were five sums we had
 to do from each of these cards and I done my sums and the teacher came round and he marked the sums and there was one he marked wrong. The others were right you see and he marked this one wrong. He said, you'll - you'll have to - get that sum right you k
n
ow. And I tried it again and I got the same answer. And - the schoolmaster said, well, he said, you'll have to stop in until that's finished. He said, you'll have to get that right. He said, you'll have to stop in. So there was only me, you see, and the s
c
hoolmaster and - I worked away and I got the same answer again. The schoolmaster said, well that's rather funny. And - he went and got his answer book you see, he'd been taking the answers from the book that he'd got. And he worked it out himself and he g
ot exactly the same answer as I got, you see. Oh, he said, this - this answers wrong. And he was ever so sorry about that, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Very bad of the printers letting an error like that through wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. But I can't remember any other incident where there was a mistake in the - answers or anything, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your mother and father take an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well they - - they liked to think I was getting on all right. And I remember a remark that my father said one time, I 
went to the Technical school when I started work you see and - I was learning - engineering drawing and I said to me father, well I don't know, I'm not all that interested. I said, I don't know where - really whether it'll be any use to me, not this type 
of thing. Well, he said, my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6702427\charrsid13305173 boy,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 you learn all you can because it will always come in handy sometime. That was the attitude that he got, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you were at school did they ever come up to the school and meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No, I - there was no - really no necessity because - I 'll tell you this, the teachers always treated me pretty good. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you left school would you have liked to have stayed on longer if you could have done?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well, not exactly - no, I didn't exactly want t
o stay on and - my - my father - really didn't want me to go into building, you see. But oh I wanted to go and do the work in the building you see. So it was my fault that I went in the building. And - perhaps it would have been better if I'd gone into so
me other work but still I don't know - I - I haven't had a bad life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 In the school were there any gangs or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6702427\charrsid13305173 groups}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  of children who ganged up - any fighting between gangs or cliques at all in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well we - we used to have - have gangs who'd
 say go against each other - in more or less a friendly manner. It - there - there were - incidents sometimes where there were boys got fighting. There was a big boy named Gray - he was bigger than most of the boys - and during playtime one day he - smack
e
d one of the other boys smaller than himself and my brother-in-law, he wasn't so big by any means, he didn't like to see this and so he said to this other boy, well, we'll challenge that boy tonight after school. Because of course fighting wasn't allowed 
in the school but - and - in - in the school playground. And so - they challenged this boy to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 have}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 a fight outside of the place called the top of the Green - that's the Green I mentioned, you see. And we all - oh, a lot of us, we went and watched it and oh that was a scrap - these two fought the one you see. That boy didn't do any smacking again.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did he come off the worse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, he got the worst of it. With the two of them of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - I
 don't know that I've had any real regrets but I - I sometimes feel - I wish I'd had a better chance to go in a higher type of education. You see all education I've got I've had to more or less do myself. Through my own efforts you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 There was a grammar school in the town at that time wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Yes, but you see then - people had to pay you see. They - people had to pay to go to the grammar school in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Could your father have afforded to pay if he'd wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 We
ll I - I daresay he could have done - but I don't know. We weren't all that well off you know. But we were better - better off than some - some of the working classes you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I wondered if there were other people of about your father's income who sent their sons there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I can't think of anybody - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You say your father didn't want you to go into the building?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. He -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What did he want you to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well he wanted me to - well, go into some - what he thought was better work, He
 didn't give me any definite - idea of what he thought I ought to go in for but he - he - thought the building - it was rather a precarious sort of job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 In what sense - in the money way you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes - money way and sometimes you see that - a lo
t of - builders you see with the contracts and the altering of prices and all that sort of things it's a precarious job. Quite of number of builders they go bankrupt you see. And - of course my - my father thought I ought to try and - get into a different
 job you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But you went into the building?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, because I - I - what I liked was I liked working among wood, you see, I liked making things, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Had you been doing this for some time - making things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, well I - as a boy I always - well I showed you that head didn't I? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173 
Well I - I always tried to make things and - I remember I was very fond old soldiers - those lead soldiers and of course they were fairly dear in those }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6702427\charrsid13305173 days}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6444694\charrsid13305173  and so I used to draw some on cardboard and I draw some soldiers on horseback you see and get a little bit of wood and nail two together so that they stood up you see and so you could make an army like that. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Things like that I used to do. And - I - was rather fond of keeping white mice and - guinea pigs and 
rabbits. I used to make the - the cubs and the little hutches for them to - yes. I remember making the white mice - house, kind of a house and I made like a little run like a staircase - not only it was straight - not steps, for them to go - and it was a 
t
hree storied place. And - they're - the nest was right up in the top by the roof and - instead of putting glass I'd got a lot of umbrella wires and made like little bars so that the - just close enough that they wouldn't be able to get out you see. And al
s
o I made a - little wheel thing - a kind of cage, perhaps you've seen them have you? And the mice - the mouse - there's a hole in one side and a - of the cage - it goes round and round you see and goes towards a hole in the cage itself. Well then the mous
e goes through there and gets in and he loves that - it's a lot of exercise, and he keeps pawing and that goes round and round and round. Things like that I used to like to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you went into the work you were thirteen - is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Fourteen. Fourteen, yes. See at that age - at that time the school leaving age was fourteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What was your starting pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 My - oh, well, you see, an apprentice had to pay somewhere around twenty pounds and the father - the parents had to pay about
 twenty pounds for an apprentice in the joinery and - then - my uncle had got the - he was doing the - was in charge of the building then. Not the one I was apprenticed under but the one who was - the - master builder. And he used to pay me half a crown a
 week. Well of course I thought that was very nice as a boy of fourteen and then of course as time went on I got - when I was an improver I had a pound a week. Well, you see, a good many of proper tradesmen got about a pound a week then and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What was an improver?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well, an improver, you see an apprentice went for - was apprenticed for somewhere about - three years und and improver had about a six years course for improving. He gradually got better and better because of course some of the technical
 parts of joinery you know are very complicated. See you have to know all about how - how to work in different angles and instead of having to mess about with them well you cut that angle to make another angle fit up against it you see, and various other 
things. See you have to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So after the three years as an apprentice did you serve nine years as an improver then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - yes, I went through my improve - yes - and you see by the time the improver finished - was finished - the improver period was
 finished there war started - that first great war started, you see, then of course I went into the - war work then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you first went into your family firm can you tell me who was there - there was your uncle Reuben and then there was the uncle who
 was the master builder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, that was uncle Thomas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And who were the other two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well the - there were no others then. Oh when I first went in? No, no there was no others then. Of course my other - the oth
er brothers had - two of the brothers, Arthur and Ted, the one I was named after had gone out to Australia quite a long time before. Then - my father's brother - older brother than him named Frank, he'd gone to do that sort of work in the mill - at Bliss'
s Tweed Mill. That mill I showed you - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So there were only four of you then were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 In - in my father's family? Well there were - there were two brothers who went out to Australia.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I mean when you started working in the family firm there were just yourself, your father and two uncles ; is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Just - just - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Any other people - masons and people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh there were - there were cousins - there were - some of - in the mason work. They were cousins of my fathe
r but there were no cousins of mine in the building. No - no first cousins of mine then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were there any other non relatives employed in the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes, quite a number. Yes. I'm sorry, I've been trying to find a photograph.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You say at one time your uncle had a hundred men working for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What time would that be? In the nineteenth }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 century}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, it was in the nineteenth century. It was before the first great war had started and of course they were men 
he - used to pick up you see when he'd got a lot of work about. He hadn't always got a hundred men working for him but he very often got perhaps thirty or - sometimes twenty, sometimes thirty. It's depended upon what work he'd got about you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were there any other building firms in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 
There was a man named Lewis and - and there were Borages and - there was as man named Sharman and -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Who had the most work of the firms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well I think we had some of the best work. I don't know that we had the most work but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you say the best you mean it required the most skill and architecture?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes. Although there were some good workmen you know altogether - on the other firms - good workmen. I think most of - in the woodw
ork especially I think most of the joinery and carpentry men were as good as you'd get anywhere in England you see. And - what I was going to say was, the builders you see used to get contracts with places like the union, the workhouse, when had to be rep
a
irs and when people died. You see, there was the undertaking and all that to do as well. And - died - you see, well, it didn't matter who go the contract you see, the - they had to make a coffin for those people who died. That - that was in their contract
. And that was given each quarter - each quarter of the year to one builder and a quarter to the others. And that's how it went on you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you were working there what were your hours when you started?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well when I started we were working te
n hours a day. Yes. I had to go as a boy I had to go at six o'clock in the morning and - I had to go to my uncle Reuben's, that was the one I was apprenticed under, because he was in charge of the joiner's shop. I had to go to his place, lock the door, he
 
used to give me the keys and I used to go and unlock all the shops you see. And - then he'd come along - they'd - the - the other men used to come to their time you see. Because I had to go a little bit before six you see. Well then we worked until eight 
o'clock and then we - had half an hour for breakfast and then worked until twelve. And then we worked until six o'clock at night, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was Saturdays the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Saturdays - at that time when I was apprenticed you see, they finished working the whole of the Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So what time did you knock off on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 At twelve o'clock. Twelve o'clock, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you ever work on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No. No, the only time that work was done on Sundays was - perhaps my father and his brother, you
 know, my uncle Reuben, if there was a coffin to make and it had to be - had to be up straight away. Only in cases like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What about holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well you see, in that - in those days they used to always - have a holiday on the Bank Ho
lidays but you didn't get any - didn't get paid for it. Oh no, there was no pay. Any time you lost you see, any time you didn't work, you lost the pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So you never had a weeks holiday then? Or did you take a weeks holiday unpaid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - not a weeks holiday. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Just the Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, just the Bank Holidays, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How did you get on with your relations - when you worked with them - how did you find them to work with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh, found them quite all right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What was your Uncle Reuben like - you told me he had very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 high}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  standards of workmanship didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Oh yes. Oh he was a - very strict - very strict and he was a very outspoken man. And - no - beating about the bush, if he - if he wanted to tell anyone what he thought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But your Uncle Thomas was the head was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What was he like to get on with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Oh - pretty good. Yes. I remember - when - just before he died - some time before he died - he wanted me to go - by the way I'd come back fro
m the war when I went - when he died and - he had - during my apprentice times I think I told you that - I used to - if hadn't got much work to do I used to do a bit of modelling and all that sort of thing. I should - with putty. I showed you that - I sho
w
ed you that putty man did I? Well - and I - modelled - one or two different things. There was a horses head and - there was an Indian with feathers in his head, you know, and various other - models like that, on glass - on pieces - small pieces of glass. 
I
 stood them up along a shelf in the shop. One morning when I went along to - and opened up the shop all those things were missing. And I wondered wherever in the world they'd gone. And - I didn't find out 'til - oh for a long time and one day Uncle - this
 
Uncle who in - who - was the employer he said, I want you to go along to your house and I want you to put a shelf up in the larder. So I went along and before I went into the larder my auntie called me in and - I think she gave me a cup of tea or somethin
g. I can't quite remember. And there were all these pieces along by his bookcase. He'd taken them all along.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But why had he never said anything to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 It - nobody said anything at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But why do you think he didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh, I think he was rather proud of it - I don't know. He showed his friends you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But he never said anything to you about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. And my other Uncle, well whether he knew I don't know - the one I was apprenticed under.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What did you think when you saw them all there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - I - I began to think, oh well, perhaps they are of some use after all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How long had it been since }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6702427\charrsid13305173 you\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  seen them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh I should think for - two or three months. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You thought never to see them again I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Oh I - I wasn't worried over it because you know it was just I did it to - to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 It's interesting that he never said anything to you about it and you just saw them there at the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How did you get on with the other people there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Oh quite all right. But you see, some of the people weren't in the shop - you see, they were different jobs all over the place. Yes. And - oh they were - quite all right you know. Funny little things happened sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - there was a - a time when the Oddfellows Hall was being built and there was a man named Randal and he always liked a smoke you know but - my uncle wouldn't allow any smoking on any buildings when they were being built and - the - this - but
 Randal was a labourer. And - the building was got up - oh, fairish height and - somebody said, oh here's Thomas coming. And he'd got his pipe going you see. So he thought Thomas was coming up one side of the building that he generally came up so he start
ed to go round the other corner and met him. And - but - Uncle didn't say such a lot. He didn't make a big fuss about it. Of course he didn't like it of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was there a big distinction between the craftsmen and the labourers then in the firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - at that time at the - if you were going apprenticed them days of course there was a distinction. A distinction when a mason had got a labourer. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 
You see a stone mason or a - a bricky - when they'd got a labourer of course the - labourer was in a different category altogether you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
You see, for a stone mason - a stone-mason needed a labourer to measure out the stones so that they could follow in their courses properly. And that was the work - the labourer - a good labourer, there was a difference b
etween a good labourer and a poor one. See a good labourer he'd - he'd see to the wants of the - of the mason. And of course there were times when a mason's work was a bit intricate you know. And - of course - there was that distinction. Now there were so
m
e labourers all they could do was to mix up mortar, you see, and do things like that, you see. Well they - of course, they - they were known as being, oh this sort of man or that sort of man you know. No distinction in the prices - in the money prices you
 see - between labourers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 They'd be paid the same even if one was much more skilled man than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Of the labourers - yes. But a mason, he had his - he had just a little less than a joiner you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You were in an interesting position because it was your family firm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Did you think at that time that there was a conflict of interest between workers and employers - did you think about that kind of thing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well not this - not the same as there is today since the uni
ons took such a - big interest in the position of the worker. Not so much then in those days. But you see, a man working in those days, he always realized that if he didn't come up to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 scratch
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  he - he'd get the sack. And you see he took - he had to take it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you belong to a trade union at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
I didn't belong to a trade union when I was working then but - after the war you see, well you had to more or less belong to a trade union if you - if you worked in any - building firm, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So when you got back after the war you went back to the firm didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
No. I didn't go straight back to the firm. I went into - when I came back I went into - a place down at - Addlestone and you remember - perhaps you'll remember, I don't know whether you
 would - there was a man named - a Frenchman named Bleriot was the first -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Your father went to work there didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Was - oh you've got that recorded have you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You told me about that right at the beginning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Your father went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And did you go there too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I went there when I got back from the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And you worked there in his woks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. For - for a time and then owing to an incident for - with my mate I was working with I thought well it
's not much use me stopping here like this because it might happen to me. You see - my mate had made just one little mistake on a motor windscreen and by putting a screw a little bit too tight he'd cracked the - a little bit of the glass of the windscreen
. And - the foreman came and told him to get his cards you see. Well I thought well if - if you can be put off for just a thing like that it's not much use me stopping. So I got a job at the - at the Great Western Railway works.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Were you still doing joinery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Down at Swindon. Yes. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And then after that did you go back to the family firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I - yes. Yes I came - I came back to the family firm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And doing joinery there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you stay on there the rest of your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. After a while I - went into a - well it wasn't a partnership really - with my brother-in-law and we worked together }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6702427\charrsid13305173 for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  a while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Just the two of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, one or two men. My brother-in-law was a responsible man, he - employed o
ne or two other men you see. But somehow or other the - the firm didn't last, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So it would be true to say that you worked at the aerodrome factory later on but it was repairing the aeroplanes in the woodwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 It - it - it wasn't a factory - it was the aerodrome - the aerodrome part - the military end of it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And you were doing repairs there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Doing repairs on the planes and on equipment - all that sort of thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But your life's work has been as a joiner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Mainly, yes. Mainly as a joiner, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 That's been your paid work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. Of course - the - the aircraft work is rather different and - well it's a different type of work you see and - more or less looked upon as being - well, a better class of w
ork then - higher class of work. Because you had to be very exacting. You see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What was your sort of title then - what were you called in the work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh they - they called you a carpenter. Yes. And - you see some of the repairs you had to d
o - if you didn't do them properly you see it might mean a man losing his life. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was there any attempt to get your firm to become unionised before the war or was there no sort of talk of that in the building trade?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You never had any contact with trade unions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
No. No. No. That - during those days and just before the war you see - a lot of the country firms, they didn't trouble about the trade union movement you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But you didn't ever have any organisers coming along and talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well there - there used to be - used to be people come and talk about the organisations. In fact it was before the war that there was the big strike at Bliss's Tweed Mill, you see, but with regard to building the building trade 
from my standpoint - there was nothing much to do about the - about that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You told me you went into the work because you liked the wood so much - did you continue }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 liking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  it - did you always like the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, yes, I liked - I liked it, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you ever regret that you'd gone in for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well there were some times when I used to - see some people, they seemed to be in - well - a little bit better off than me. I used to sometimes think, well, why can't I get into somethin
g that'll give me a bit better chance, you see. But, you see, when - when I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 working in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 the - in among the aircraft I was quite happy and the pay wasn't too bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Do you think you would have preferred another occupation looking back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - ye
s. You see, I told you I think that during the war I qualified as a - a physiotherapist. And I should like to have been - I should have preferred to have been a physiotherapist but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 To have earned your living that way you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. But the dif
ficulty was that a lot of the - a lot of the places were full up you see. What I was saying was that - a lot of the people who wanted to employ a physiotherapist, they wanted you to do all odd jobs when they hadn't go to the other work about. Well - that 
m
ade me realize that, well - it couldn't be a very good business you see. And - also, I realized that I shouldn't be any better off, you see, I was a married man. I shouldn't be any better off if I - took that sort of thing on. And then I used to take in t
he - a magazine that was to deal with all that sort of work, I forget now of that thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 This was after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you were getting this half a crown when you first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 started}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  work, what did you spend it on - did you give any to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - perhaps to - give her - something - some part of it. There used to be some boys papers I used to buy. Sweets if you wanted them and - save a bit. Saved a bit, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 How did you save?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh I had a money box - put it in money box.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did she expect you to give her a regular sum?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No, not really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So some weeks would it be true to say you spent it all on savings and papers and that kind of thing or fid you give her some every week?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - she sometimes might say, take a little something, you see or - or - well, or father - then I'd got a sister you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But by and large the money was your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you were getting a pound then did you give any for your keep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. I can't just remember what the - I used to give. I can't remember that - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So when you were an apprentice - for the first three years - who bought your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh, mother and father, yes. Well - father of course. It was his money of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you were getting a pound did they continue to buy your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh, I had to buy my own then. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And you always lived at home up to the time you went away didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Until the war started, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 In what ways did your life change when you started working full time - socially and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What do you mean when I was...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you get to know a new lot of people - did you have a different sort of social life when you were working after you'd left school?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh - well
 - I had some very happy times. We used to have - I think you saw that photograph of the choir. The - well I used to - before that of course - I used to belong to a choir called the Temperance Choir. And I used to sing contralto then. And - I used to love
 going to those practices and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You carried on with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Right through your teens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. Then I belonged to the - joined the choir at the Baptist - at the chapel. And do you remember the chapel where the organ - up where the organ
 was - that was where the choir used to sit up there - 'course we are not big enough now we all sit down - well there's only about half a dozen of us. Get together as a choir if you could call it that. And - we used to have altogether about thirty in our 
choir you know. And - I first of all singing baritone and the - conductor of the choir, he said to me one day, he said, oh Ted I think you ought to go on the other side and go with the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 tenor}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 , he said, you - you'll find your voice is - will be ever so much better as a tenor. And so of course after that I - I've been singing tenor, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Ever since?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you continue to go for these long walks and that sort of thing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh - well - we - we used to - well I wouldn't say long walks, on
ly occasionally long walks but we used to do the running - used to do the running and go a four and a half - sometimes the four or - say a six mile, it depended - a six mile run you see. With a - what they called the Chipping Norton Harriers at that time.
 I used to do that, yes, but of course I was getting a bit older then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I'm talking now about the time you left school up to when you went away to war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 From the age of about fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 To about twenty-five when you went away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes, that was the time. That was the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You did a lot - in physical culture then didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. I used to - I think I - did I tell you - how I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You told me about how you went to the gymnasium and all that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 That had started at school hadn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You began as school and then you carried on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did your life change in any major way when you started work - did it not make much difference in your life, in your interests and that 
sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - I think it seemed to sort of work in automatically in a way of speaking. You see, we got a lot of concerts and things from the chapel work you see. And - then there were other organisations started, we - we used to - go round an
d - different - there was a - a gymnasium now and we used to give a bit of a display for the gymnasium and things like that. And - then - we used to have concerts - the choir used to go round to the villages and give concerts. And Christmas times we - our
 
choir, as I say there were about thirty in our choir at one time, we used to go round carol singing the - the fortnight before Christmas you see, and - we used to collect and of course we collected somewhere about twenty pounds - most Christmasses, and th
at was a lot in those days, wouldn't be much today but - then that was divided up among the poor people. Yes. And - they made up parcels with say tea, sugar and - various things you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6702427\charrsid13305173  know nd}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  sent round to people who were very poor. Well of course you don't g
et those very poor today like - but people were very poor in those days. And - the - of course it was a bit of a God send to some people you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Would you say that working full time changed your attitude to life in any way in those first years of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - I - I don't know that it did. It - it probably made you say - take more command of yourself because you see you'd got to - do your work and keep yourself to that sort of thing and - then of course you'd got to make your amusement after and 
you didn't get just the amount of time to - have the same amusement. But I - I don't know it seemed to - we seemed to amuse ourselves all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When you went to a choir practice would it be after eight o'clock then that you'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6702427\charrsid13305173 go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 It was generally somewhere about - say sometimes half past seven or eight like it is to - these days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You'd go straight from work then would you when you finished work at eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh no, no, not - not eight. It was six o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 At six you finished work did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. Yes. Yes. Eventually - later on before - before the war it got - it was half past five. That was when - when it was on full time. Then there was full time and short time you see, in the winter when people couldn't see to do their 
work - in the same manner of course they were put on short time. And of course we - we'd got the gas in the shop - then. Gas. You - and you used to have a big long pipe coming down over the bench and a bracket coming out and there was just a little burner
 you see and a - a fan shaped flame. That's all you had to - work from. And yet we never set fire to anything. That was all - a naked flame you see. Then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6702427\charrsid13305173 eventually}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  there was the - oh what did they call it - the mantle burner came and then of course we thought that was a wonderful light then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 At this time did you make any new friends, did you have any girl friends at that time or go to dances - before the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - I never went to dance because - well - some people to think you - dances weren't 
all that good you know. And - but it wasn't from that standpoint so much, I was - wasn't interested all that much, but - we used to mix up with what you might call a - a gang from the chapel and - they - you'd get young ladies and young men mix up and - y
o
u'd go out for walks - all the gang go out and very often after the chapel at night on Sundays perhaps we'd walk right round the park walls rather - that's walk about three or four miles you see, and we'd sing and people used to say how - how lovely it us
ed to sound because we took the parts you see. We used to sing at the top of our voices and have jokes you know or - oh we used to enjoy ourselves. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 So did you all keep together as a group or did you pair off with special}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6702427\charrsid13305173 
 girl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  or boy friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - as - different people did pair off but you see, my wife was - a Primitive Methodist and I was a Baptist and - I knew my wife from - because I was friendly with her brother, that brother who - padded his trousers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 The brother-in-law?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes, he was a - I was friendly with him you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And your families were friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
My family was friendly with them yes. And that's how I knew her. But - I didn't pair off because of - being in the gang you see. Although of course there were some young ladies I rather liked. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Had you started courting before you went to the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Yes. Yes. Yes. And - of course I used to get letters from her and used to send letters to her. In fact, I wasn't married when I sent her those two - I sho
wed you those didn't I - those two books with a vellum - and I sent her some moon - moon - stones from - Bombay and I sent her a coral necklace and she lost that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 coral}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  necklace and she went into a restaurant some - some while after and - she was a - she wasn't sure but she was almost - almost sure that she saw a woman with them on. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 She'd evidently lost them and so the woman picked them up. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
But she - you can't be absolutely sure of that can you? Well I also sent her a - now what was the other things I sent her - sent her one or two things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But you didn't have the occasion of introducing her to your mother because I suppose your mother knew her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you bring friends home to tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. We - oh yes, we used to have friends come to tea. Fairly often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 If you went out in the evening did your mother expect you to tell her where you were going and when you'd be back or was it up to you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What, through the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Before you went to the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh - oh I 
see what you mean. Well - not exactly and yet she liked to know and of course she'd worry if I was a bit extra late getting home but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did you have a set time you were expected to be in by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well - the - do you say expected to be back? Well they 
didn't like you to be out say after ten o'clock. And - of course if you could get in a bit earlier that was all the better. But - they didn't like you to be out 'til say if you were out at twelve o'clock then they worried. Because they began to wonder wha
t was happening you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Did they like to meet any of your new friends or did they know all these people you used to go around with anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well they knew - they knew most of the - most of the people who used to come to the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 They'd known them for quite a time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes - but occasionally there'd be some new friends }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6702427\charrsid13305173 come}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  you see. And - like my mother was - liked a bit of company you know really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You were encouraged to bring your friends home were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. And - my - my s
ister worked at that same place as my wife you see, before the war and - my wife was the head - sewing - heading the sewing department you see and - my sister was working under her and she used to come up to - to our place to tea. That was before I'd - st
arted courting her and - it was half through that that I got to - know her - got to know her as - in the way I wanted to then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Because she came round to you - house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes, but I - of course I'd known her ever since she was a little girl. I never dream I should marry her you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You were saying about the saw pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes. Yes, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 during}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  - my boyhood days, my early boyhood days that was, before I was actually apprenticed I used to go along to the yard there which - which I showed you. And 
- they used to have the old fashioned saw pits there and they were somewhere about eight feet deep and I should think they'd be about - anywhere about - eight to ten feet long and they used to put some - quartering across and rest a big tree on top of the
 
quartering and there used to be a man down in the pit with a - a guard over his eyes so that the sawdust didn't get in him eyes and - there was another man up on top of the tree and I should have said that before that they'd marked all around the tree - t
h
ey'd marked the size of the boards that they'd got to cut down. And they cut down, right through the tree by hand with a great big saw with big teeth - the man at the top with the double handles pushing down - the man at the bottom pulling down and they'd
 saw for hours and hours and hours - through that thick trees - ever such thick }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 trees}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 , and it was quite }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 laborious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  work you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 
There was two of those sawpits up there in that - place at that time and - eventually the - my grandfather got a - a big circular saw with a - an engine with a great big strap from a big wheel on the engine to a little wheel on the saw bench. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Then they used to cut the trees down with that. And - then eventually you see, the it was cheaper to get the timer already cut because they we
re beginning to - sell timber already cut in - and so of course that - that was all done away with then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When did they go over to the engine - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh that - that was before I went into the firm actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 seeing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  these saw men as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Oh yes. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 
Yes, I remember an old man, he was a stout old man used to be at the top and a - a thinner man down below and I used to wonder what it could be like with having all that sawdust coming down on you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Because he'd got to be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 able}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 to follow the - the line down underneath there you see. And then I told you about the - banker work didn't I? Well - they also up at that yard you see they used to have great big blocks of freestone used to come in and there used to be
 two men used to saw the freestone down with a great big saw in a similar manner to what they used to cut the timber down like that. Whatever sizes they wanted - they wanted for - say windowsills, mullions and bessemers and all those sort of things and th
ey had to saw that down but you see that all had to be trimmed up land made to shape. Well then they got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 banker masons}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 doing that sort of work in a - in a little old shed and of course they - they had to be pretty good people at that work. Because they'd go
t to get everything absolutely straight and true or if there were any mouldings they had to get the mouldings done that mouldings would fit the next lot you see. And you've perhaps seen some of the shapes in windows - stone part. Well they had to do all t
hat sort of thing and - then of course that was banker masons work you see, what we saw in the church - all that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 reading}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
 up there. Well when the banker}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
mason did that you see, the next block that had to come on and to fit against that so they had to be very good people at that sort of work. Well I told you about the old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 banker}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  mason who in the winter, didn't I, with the snow on top of the shed - I told you that did I? No. Well - I - I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 working}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  then at that time and my uncle had sent me along to get some t
imber to take along to the joiners shop because at that yard all the building timer was stacked. The joinery timber at the joinery yard and - it was - the snow was somewhere about a foot deep and - the - this shop where the banker mason was working - bank
e
r masons were working and it was a little tin - roofed shed you see and they'd got a little tiny fire there. I went in and said to a man working there at one of the pieces, my word I said, Alfie you - you haven't got much fire there. No, he said, we haven
't. I said, and you're roof looks a little bit caving in with all that snow on the top. He said, yes, about two more flakes of snow and two sparrows and down it'll come. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 You had this little group of people and you used to discuss things didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 When did you form that group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 
Well - it was called actually the Christian Endeavour. One of the groups. And - the Christian Endeavour then - I don't know whether there's any of it about now - it was formed of young people genera
lly but of course the older people used to come and you'd have discussions on the various - topics that - and - one - one discussion I rather remember was, whether it was right for a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3760673\charrsid13305173 
Christian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173  to go to a theatre. Well in those days people had very narrow views you see and - oh, we got up to quite a - quite a head over things you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Your family and you didn't disapprove of theatres did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well they - they were - didn't trouble a great lot but I don't think they liked the idea of going much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 It didn't arise very often in Chipping Norton did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 What about the W.E.A. - when did you get involved with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well that was after I'd started work really and they used to have some very good classes at - I showed you t
he old Guild Hall didn't I? Well the upper part of that which is now used by the - by Town Clerk and the corporation - all the corporation workers - like in the clerking like - that top part used to be used as a - a - a W.E.A. place. And - I learned my fi
rst aid up there. Yes. And - I learned book keeping and - also French and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Was that all before the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes. But - yes, and also I told you I went in for the engineering drawing. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 I think you said that was at the Technical School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Well it was at the Technical - they - they called it, yes, but it was a W.E.A. - a W.E.A. - works you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 It was run by the W.E.A.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Run by - the W.E.A. They called it the Technical school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 But it was part of the Workers Educational Movement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14761640 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11886869 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14306447\charrsid13305173 And what about when you did a bit of philosophy - was that later?
